The White Hoods : an Historical Romance is a historical novel by Anna Eliza Bray first published in 1828 in London .
Inspector French and the Starvel Tragedy is a crime novel by Freeman Wills Crofts , featuring Inspector Joseph French of Scotland Yard .
Stirrings Still is the final prose piece by Samuel Beckett , written 1986 - -89 to give his American publisher , Barney Rosset , something to publish .
The Fabled Fourth Graders of Aesop Elementary School is a 2007 children 's novel by Candace Fleming .
Gauntlgrym is a novel released in October 2010 , written by fantasy author R. A. Salvatore set in the Forgotten Realms campaign world .
Family Without a Name ( French : Famille - sans - nom ) is an 1889 adventure novel by Jules Verne about the life of a family in Lower Canada ( present - day Quebec ) during the Lower Canada Rebellion of 1837 and 1838 that sought an independent and democratic republic for Lower Canada .
On the Frontiers is volume thirteen in the French comic book ( or bande dessinée ) science fiction series Valérian and Laureline created by writer Pierre Christin and artist Jean - Claude Mézières .
Building Big is a book written by David Macaulay , author of the book series The Way Things Work .
French Without Tears is a comic play written by a 25-year - old Terence Rattigan in 1936 .
Tip and Trade is a 2011 book by Canadian author Mark Coakley that depicts an insider trading conspiracy involving Wall Street lawyer Gil Corblum and another lawyer , Stan Grmovsek , who were found to have gained over $ 10 million in illegal profits over a 14-year span .
When I Was Mortal is a short story collection by the Spanish writer Javier Marías .
Eyes of the Calculor is a post - apocalyptic novel by Sean McMullen published in 2001 .
The Pain and the Great One is a children 's picture book published in 1974 , written by Judy Blume and illustrated by Irene Trivas .
`` The Thing in the Moonlight '' is a short story by J. Chapman Miske , based on a letter from H. P. Lovecraft to Donald Wandrei , dated November 24 , 1927 .
The Dungeons & Dragons Gazetteer was written by Gary Holian , Erik Mona , Sean Reynolds , and Frederick Weining , and published in 2000 .
The Mother Tongue ( ISBN 0 - 380 - 71543 - 0 ) is a book by Bill Bryson which compiles the history and origins of the English and the language 's various quirks .
Hayduke Lives ! ( ISBN 0 - 316 - 00411 - 1 ) , written in 1989 by Edward Abbey , is the sequel to the popular book The Monkey Wrench Gang .
Fire Study is a 2008 fantasy novel written by Maria V. Snyder .
Pereira Maintains ( Italian : Sostiene Pereira ) is a 1994 novel by the Italian writer Antonio Tabucchi .
Captains and the Kings is a 1972 historical novel by Taylor Caldwell chronicling the rise to wealth and power of an Irish immigrant , Joseph Francis Xavier Armagh , who emigrates as a penniless teenager to the United States , along with his younger brother and baby sister , only for their parents to die shortly afterwards .
The Disk is a 1975 short story written by Argentinian writer Jorge Luis Borges .
The Fine Art of Mixing Drinks is a book about cocktails by David A. Embury , first published in 1948 .
Meet Me at the Monkey Trees is a local interest children 's picture book that was written and illustrated by Sarah McEvoy .
The Shoulder of Shasta is a romance novel by Bram Stoker written in 1895 .
Loss and Gain is a philosophical novel by John Henry Newman published in 1848 .
All for Australia is a 1984 book by Australian historian Professor Geoffrey Blainey .
Grundlagen der Mathematik ( English : Foundations of Mathematics ) is a two - volume work by David Hilbert and Paul Bernays .
I 'm Not Who You Think I Am is an American novel for young adults by Peg Kehret , published in 1999 .
Hairy Maclary 's Bone , first published in 1984 , is the second of the series of books by New Zealand author Lynley Dodd featuring Hairy Maclary .
The Civil War in the United States is a collection of articles on the American Civil War by Karl Marx and Friedrich Engels for the New York Tribune and Die Presse of Vienna between 1861 and 1862 , and correspondence between Marx and Engels between 1860 and 1866 .
The Mother / Child Papers is Alicia Ostriker 's fourth book of poetry .
Cibola Burn is a 2014 science fiction novel by James S. A. Corey ( pen name of Daniel Abraham and Ty Franck ) and the fourth book in The Expanse series .
Midnight Rain is a paranormal romantic suspense novel by Holly Lisle , published in 2004 , the first novel of this type Lisle has published .
The Poet of Tolstoy Park is the 2005 debut novel of Sonny Brewer , published by Ballantine .
Divine Comedies is the seventh book of poetry by James Merrill ( 1926 - -1995 ) .
The Odd Women is an 1893 novel by the English novelist George Gissing .
`` The Gambler , the Nun , and the Radio '' is a short story by Ernest Hemingway published in his collection of short stories The Snows of Kilimanjaro .
Asterix and Caesar 's Gift is the twenty - first volume of the Asterix comic book series , by René Goscinny ( stories ) and Albert Uderzo ( illustrations ) .
Encyclopedia of American Biography , a biographical encyclopedia , by John A. Garraty ( ed . ) and Jerome L. Sternstein ( assoc . ed . ) This encyclopedia , published by Harper & Row in 1974 , `` is more than a storehouse of information ....
Finger Lickin ' Fifteen is a 2009 novel by Janet Evanovich that continues the saga of Stephanie Plum , bounty hunter in Trenton , NJ .
The Purple Land is a novel set in 19th century Uruguay by William Henry Hudson , first published in 1885 under the title The Purple Land that England Lost .
Excellent Women is a novel by Barbara Pym , first published in 1952 , her second published novel and generally acclaimed as the funniest and most successful of her comedies of manners .
Tactics of Mistake is a science fiction novel written by Gordon R. Dickson which was first published as a serial in Analog in 1970 - 1971 .
Deliberate Prose - Essays 1952 to 1995 is a collection of essays penned by Allen Ginsberg in the years 1952 to 1995 .
Joe Gould 's Secret is a 1965 book by Joseph Mitchell , based upon his two New Yorker profiles , `` Professor Sea Gull '' ( 1942 ) and `` Joe Gould 's Secret '' ( 1964 ) .
Guy Domville is a play by Henry James first staged in London in 1895 .
King Matt the First ( Polish : Król Maciuś Pierwszy ) is a children 's novel by Polish author , physician , and child pedagogue Janusz Korczak .
Hipparchicus is the name usually given to Ἱππαρχικός , Hipparchikós , one of the two treatises on horsemanship by the Athenian historian and soldier Xenophon ( c. 430 -- 354 BC ) .
Ausculta Fili ( Latin , literally `` Give ear , my son '' ) is a letter addressed 5 December 1301 , by Pope Boniface VIII to Philip the Fair , King of France .
The Tiger Rising is a 2001 children 's book written by Newbery Medal winning author Kate DiCamillo .
A Spaceship Built of Stone and Other Stories is a 1987 science fiction short story collection by Lisa Tuttle , her second after A Nest of Nightmares ( 1985 ) .
Emerald Germs of Ireland ( 2001 ) is a black comedy novel by Irish writer Patrick McCabe .
Phra Aphai Mani ( Thai : พระอภัยมณี ) is a 30,000-line epic written by Thailand 's best - known poet , Sunthorn Phu .
The Broken Window is a crime thriller novel written by Jeffery Deaver , published in 2008 .
Run Before the Wind is the second novel in the Will Lee series by Stuart Woods , written as a semi - sequel to his first novel Chiefs .
Considerations on Representative Government is a book by John Stuart Mill published in 1861 .
Aalaap mein girah ( Hindi : आलाप में गिरह ) is the first collection of poems by Hindi poet Geet Chaturvedi , published in Hindi in 2010 by Rajkamal Prakashan , New Delhi .
The Trainer is a play by David Wilson and Anne Aylor ( with writing contributions from composer Keith Burstein ) .
The God Engines is a science fiction novella by John Scalzi published in 2009 .
The Phantom of Manhattan , a 1999 novel by Frederick Forsyth , is a sequel to the Andrew Lloyd Webber musical The Phantom of the Opera , itself based on the original book by Gaston Leroux .
Outlaw Pete is a book by Bruce Springsteen and artwork by Frank Caruso and based on the song of the same name from Springsteen 's album , Working on a Dream .
Lord Brocktree is a fantasy novel by Brian Jacques , published in 2000 .
Protection or Free Trade is a book published in 1886 by the economist and social philosopher , Henry George .
Songs of Travel and Other Verses is an 1896 book of poetry by Robert Louis Stevenson .
Tanya Grotter ( Russian : Таня Гроттер ) is the female protagonist of a Russian fantasy novel series by Dmitri Yemets .
The Forty Days of Musa Dagh ( German : Die vierzig Tage des Musa Dagh ) is a 1933 novel by Austrian - Bohemian writer Franz Werfel based on true events that took place in 1915 , during the second year of World War I and at the beginning of the Armenian Genocide .
We Are All Legends is a collection of fantasy short stories written by Darrell Schweitzer featuring his sword and sorcery hero Sir Julian .
Weedflower is an American children 's historial fiction novel by Cynthia Kadohata , who received the Newbery and Whiting Awards .
The Viceroy of Ouidah is a novel published in 1980 by Bruce Chatwin , a British author .
Fear Is the Key is a 1961 first - person narrative thriller novel by Scottish author Alistair MacLean .
A Little Green Book of Monster Stories is a collection of short stories written by American author Joe R. Lansdale , published by Borderlands Press as part of their `` Little Book '' series .
Gemma Bovery ( ISBN 0 - 2240 - 6114 - 3 ) is a graphic novel written by Posy Simmonds .
Libidinal Economy ( French : Economie Libidinale ) is a 1974 book by Jean - François Lyotard .
Germinie Lacerteux ( 1865 ) is a grim , anti - Romantic novel by Edmond and Jules de Goncourt in which the authors aim to present , as they say , a `` clinic of love . ''
The Jewel of Seven Stars is a 1903 horror novel by Bram Stoker .
The Hero with a Thousand Faces ( first published in 1949 ) is a seminal work of comparative mythology by Joseph Campbell .
The Literary Pocket - Book was a collection of works edited by Leigh Hunt and containing material by Hunt , Percy Bysshe Shelley , John Keats , and Bryan Waller Procter .
The 39 Clues is a series of adventure novels written by a collaboration of authors , including Rick Riordan , Gordon Korman , Peter Lerangis , Jude Watson , Patrick Carman , Linda Sue Park , Margaret Peterson Haddix , Roland Smith , David Baldacci , Jeff Hirsch , Natalie Standiford , C. Alexander London , and Jenny Goebel .
Season of Doubt is a 1968 novel written by Australian author Jon Cleary set in Beiruit .
`` The Elf Mound '' ( Danish : Elverhøi ) is a literary fairy tale by Danish poet and author Hans Christian Andersen ( 1805 - -1875 ) .
Notes from the Frontier is a non - fiction book by American author Hugh Nissenson describing life on a kibbutz in northern Israel , published in 1968 .
The Electronic Revolution is an essay collection by William S. Burroughs that was first published in 1970 by Expanded Media Editions in West Germany .
The House in Paris is Elizabeth Bowen 's fifth novel .
Seduction of the Innocent is a book by German - American psychiatrist Fredric Wertham , published in 1954 , that warned that comic books were a negative form of popular literature and a serious cause of juvenile delinquency .
The Tiger Warrior is an archaeological adventure novel by David Gibbins .
In the House of the Queen 's Beasts ( 2001 ) is a young - adult novel by Jean Thesman .
Inter Ice Age 4 ( 第四間氷期 , Dai - Yon Kampyōki ) is an early science fiction novel by Japanese writer Kōbō Abe originally serialized in the journal Sekai from 1958 to 1959 and first translated into English by American scholar E. Dale Saunders in 1970 .
No Coins , Please is a 1984 young adult book by Gordon Korman .
Les Châtiments ( `` Castigations '' ) is a collection of poems by Victor Hugo that fiercely attack the grandeur of Napoléon III 's Second Empire .
Video Night is a 2013 horror novel by American author Adam Cesare .
Loopy Ears ( Петлистые уши , Petli′stye U′shi ) is a short story by a Nobel Prize - winning Russian author Ivan Bunin which was written in 1917 and gave his posthumous 1954 collection its title .
Vimanarama is a three - issue comic book mini - series written by Grant Morrison , with art by Philip Bond , and published by the Vertigo imprint of DC Comics .
Flappers and Philosophers is the first collection of short stories written by F. Scott Fitzgerald , published in 1920 .
The Fifty Worst Films of All Time ( And How They Got That Way ) is a 1978 book by Harry Medved , with Randy Dreyfuss and Michael Medved .
The Purcell Papers ( 1880 ) are a collection of thirteen Gothic , supernatural , historical and humorous short stories by Joseph Sheridan Le Fanu ( 1814 - -73 ) originally written for the Dublin University Magazine .
Abduction ! by Peg Kehret , is a novel about a 13-year - old girl named Bonnie who searches for her brother Matt and their dog Pookie who were both abducted .
Le Chandelier is an 1835 play in three acts by French dramatist Alfred de Musset .
`` Murke 's Collected Silences '' ( German : Doktor Murkes gesammeltes Schweigen ) is a short story by German writer Heinrich Böll , first published in the Frankfurter Hefte in 1955 and in English in 1963 .
The Everlasting Man is a Christian apologetics book written by G. K. Chesterton , published in 1925 .
Get in the Van is a memoir by singer , writer , and spoken word artist Henry Rollins first published in 1994 by Rollins ' own company , 2.13.61 Publications .
Two to the Fifth is the 32nd book of the Xanth series by Piers Anthony .
There Should be More Dancing is a black comedy novel , written by Australian author Rosalie Ham .
The Second Scroll is a 1951 novel by the Jewish - Canadian writer A. M. Klein .
Miss Lonelyhearts , published in 1933 , is Nathanael West 's second novel .
Luha ng Buwaya or , `` Crocodile 's Tear '' in translation , is a 1983 novel written by Palanca Awardee and Filipino novelist Amado V. Hernandez .
Det är 1988 och har precis börjat snöa ( lit . It Is 1988 and It Has Just Started Snowing ) is a 2005 Sigge Eklund novel .
The Book of Merlyn is an Arthurian fantasy book written by T. H. White .
Simple Genius is a thriller novel by American writer David Baldacci , which topped the New York Times bestseller list for the week ending April 28 , 2007 .
On a Silver Platter is a 1990 Donald Duck comic by Don Rosa .
Codex Alera is a fantasy book series by Jim Butcher .
The End of Vandalism is a 1994 novel by American author Tom Drury .
Vaaren is a novel written by Norwegian Nobel laureate Sigrid Undset , published in 1914 .
Styles of Radical Will is a collection of essays by Susan Sontag published in 1969 .
Les Rougon - Macquart is the collective title given to a cycle of twenty novels by French writer Émile Zola .
The History of Independent Cinema is a book by film historian Phil Hall that traces the development of the United States independent film sector from silent films to digital media .
The Secret Diary of Laura Palmer is a 1990 spin - off novel from the television series Twin Peaks by Jennifer Lynch .
Mountain Cat ( a.k.a . The Mountain Cat Murders ) is a mystery novel by Rex Stout , first published in book form in 1939 .
Voyages by Starlight is a collection of science fiction and horror stories by author Ian R. MacLeod .
One Million A.D. ( ISBN 0 - 7394 - 6273 - 3 ) is a science fiction anthology edited by Gardner Dozois that was published in 2005 .
Jack 's Luck Runs Out is a full - color one - shot comic book created by Jason Little .
Prince Jellyfish is an unpublished novel by American journalist and author Hunter S. Thompson .
An Account of Corsica is the earliest piece of writing related to the Grand Tour literature that was written by the Scottish author James Boswell .
The Cat in the Hat Comes Back is a children 's book written and illustrated by Dr. Seuss and published by Random House in 1958 .
O Desertor das Letras was a heroic - comic poem which was published by Manuel Inácio da Silva Alvarenga .
You Ca n't See ' Round Corners was the first published novel by Australian author Jon Cleary .
White Dawns ( Macedonian : Бели мугри , Beli mugri ) is a collection of poems by the famous Macedonian writer Kočo Racin ( Кочо Рацин ) , published in 1939 in Samobor , near Zagreb , Croatia .
`` The Handicapped '' is a science fiction short story written in 1967 by Larry Niven , set in the Known Space universe .
Chicago Poems is a 1916 collection of poetry by Carl Sandburg , his first by a mainstream publisher .
Evolution of the Vertebrates , subtitled `` A History of the Backboned Animals Through Time '' is a basic paleontology textbook by Edwin H. Colbert , published by John Wiley & Sons .
The Mermaid Chair is a 2005 novel written by American novelist Sue Monk Kidd , which has also been adapted as a Lifetime movie .
In about 650 , the third Caliph Uthman ibn Affan ( d. 656 ) began noticing slight differences in pronunciation of the Quran as Islam expanded beyond the Arabian Peninsula into Persia , the Levant , and North Africa .
Mucho Mojo Is a mystery / crime novel by American author Joe R. Lansdale .
Kill Decision is a science fiction novel by Daniel Suarez , published in 2012 .
Philosophy and the Mirror of Nature ( published in 1979 ) is a book by American philosopher Richard Rorty .
An Enquiry Concerning Human Understanding is a book by the Scottish empiricist philosopher David Hume , published in English in 1748 .
Night of the Ripper ( 1984 ) is a novel written by American writer Robert Bloch , the author of Psycho .
The Science of Life is a book written by H. G. Wells , Julian Huxley and G. P. Wells , published in three volumes by The Waverley Publishing Company Ltd in 1929 - -30 , giving a popular account of all major aspects of biology as known in the 1920s .
Other Bells for Us to Ring ( 1990 ) is the U.S. author Robert Cormier 's first novel for young readers ( 10 - -12 years ) .
La Chamade is a 1965 novel by French playwright and novelist Françoise Sagan .
Sky Masters of the Space Force was an American , syndicated newspaper comic strip created on September 8 , 1958 by writer Dave Wood and penciler Jack Kirby , featuring the adventures of an American astronaut .
Master of Whitestorm is a science fiction / fantasy book by Janny Wurts , published in 1992 .
Psychomech is a horror novel written by Brian Lumley and published by Panther Books in 1984 .
Calculus Made Easy is a book on infinitesimal calculus originally published in 1910 by Silvanus P. Thompson , considered a classic and elegant introduction to the subject .
The Woman Who Did ( 1895 ) is a novel by Grant Allen about a young , self - assured middle - class woman who defies convention as a matter of principle and who is fully prepared to suffer the consequences of her actions .
A Small Boy and Others is a book of autobiography by Henry James published in 1913 .
The Dark Wing is a 2001 military science fiction novel by Walter H. Hunt and part one of a 4-part series .
Rogue Ship is a 1965 novel by A. E. van Vogt , created and adapted from 3 short stories to form a novel .
Exit to Eden is a 1985 novel by Anne Rice , initially published in under the pen name Anne Rampling , but subsequently under Rice 's name .
I Served the King of England ( Czech : Obsluhoval jsem anglického krále ) is a novel by the Czech writer Bohumil Hrabal .
Oh , Play That Thing ( 2004 ) is a novel by Irish writer Roddy Doyle .
`` The Sliced - Crosswise Only - On - Tuesday World '' is a science - fiction short story by Philip José Farmer , first published in 1971 in New Dimensions 1 :
Trying is a drama by Canadian - born playwright Joanna Glass that premiered at Chicago 's Victory Gardens Theater on March 29 , 2004 .
Stay in Your Own Sled ( Russian : Не в свои сани не садись , an idiom meaning `` Do n't bite off more than you can chew , '' ) is a play by Alexander Ostrovsky , written in 1852 and first published in the No.5 ( March , book 1 ) , 1853 , issue of Moskvityanin .
V. is the debut novel of Thomas Pynchon , published in 1963 .
The Secrets of Sir Richard Kenworthy is a Regency romance written by Julia Quinn and published in 2015 by Avon Books .
Y Stafell Ddirgel ( in English , The Secret Room ) is a novel by Marion Eames written in the Welsh language and first published in 1969 .
A Quiet Belief In Angels is a thriller novel written by R. J. Ellory .
The Angel Trilogy is a romance , thriller , fantasy , and supernatural series of three books written by L.A. Weatherly .
The Atlas of Middle - earth by Karen Wynn Fonstad is an atlas of J. R. R. Tolkien 's fictional realm of Middle - earth .
The Far Pavilions is an epic novel of British - Indian history by M. M. Kaye , published in 1978 , which tells the story of an English officer during the British Raj .
The Barn Owl 's Wondrous Capers is a 2007 graphic novel by Indian graphic artist Sarnath Banerjee .
The Man Who Counted ( original Portuguese title : O Homem que Calculava ) is a book on recreational mathematics and curious word problems by Brazilian writer Júlio César de Mello e Souza , published under the pen name Malba Tahan .
The Little School is a novel written by Alicia Partnoy , a woman who was `` disappeared '' during the Dirty War period of the history of Argentina .
It 's Not the End of the World is a young adult novel written by Judy Blume , published in 1972 .
At the Villa of Reduced Circumstances is a book by Scottish author and academic Alexander McCall Smith , relating further matters in the life of the main character , Professor Dr Moritz - Maria von Igelfeld .
Shakespeare and the Goddess of Complete Being is a book of literary criticism authored by Ted Hughes .
Mrs. Piggle - Wiggle is the title of a series of books by Betty MacDonald .
La Bête ( 1991 ) is a comedy by American playwright , David Hirson .
Headlong Hall is a novella by Thomas Love Peacock , his first long work of fiction , written in 1815 and published in 1816 .
Like a Hole in the Head is a 1970 thriller love story novel written by James Hadley Chase .
The Future of the Race is a 1996 book by prominent African - American scholars Henry Louis Gates and Cornel West .
The Suicide Collectors is the debut novel of American author David Oppegaard .
Shadow and Act is a collection of essays by Ralph Ellison , published in 1964 .
Coelestis Pastor was a papal encyclical issued on November 19 , 1687 by Pope Innocent XI in which he condemns the practices of the Quietists , a group of religious separatists led by Miguel de Molinos .
Les Rayons et les Ombres ( `` Beams and shadows '' , 1840 ) is a collection of forty - four poems by Victor Hugo , the last collection to be published before his exile , and containing most of his poems from between 1837 and 1840 .
Man and His Symbols is the last work undertaken by Carl Jung before his death in 1961 .
Better Angel is a novel by Forman Brown first published in 1933 under the pseudonym Richard Meeker .
Zorgamazoo ( 2008 ) is Canadian children 's author Robert Paul Weston 's first novel .
King - Cat Comics and Stories is a long - running , critically acclaimed photocopied mini - comic series , authored and self - published by John Porcellino .
English Journey is an account by J. B. Priestley of his travels in England which was published in 1934 .
Pour un nouveau roman ( translated as For a New Novel ( US ) , Towards a New Novel ( UK ) ) is a 1963 collection of theoretical writings by French author Alain Robbe - Grillet .
A Horse 's Tale is a novel by Mark Twain ( Samuel Clemens ) , written partially in the voice of Soldier Boy , who is Buffalo Bill 's favorite horse , at a fictional frontier outpost with the U.S. 7th Cavalry .
Hokas Pokas ! is a collection of science fiction stories , and the novel Star Prince Charlie by Poul Anderson and Gordon R. Dickson .
The Enola Holmes Mysteries is a young - adult fiction series of detective novels by American author Nancy Springer , starring Enola Holmes as the fourteen - year - old sister of an already - famous Sherlock Holmes , twenty years her senior .
The Vision of the Anointed is a book by economist and political columnist Thomas Sowell challenging people Sowell refers to as `` Teflon prophets , '' who predict that there will be future social , economic , or environmental problems in the absence of government intervention ( Ralph Nader is one of his foremost examples ) .
The Origin and Development of the Moral Ideas is a book by the Finnish philosopher Edvard Westermarck , published between 1906 and 1908 .
The Angel 's Luck Series is a group of three science fiction novels by Joe Clifford Faust , beginning with his first novel , 1989 's Desperate Measures .
The Postman is a post - apocalyptic science fiction novel by David Brin .
The Revolution of Everyday Life ( French : Traité de savoir - vivre à l’usage des jeunes générations ) is a 1967 book by Raoul Vaneigem , Belgian author , philosopher and one time member of the Situationist International ( 1961 - -1970 ) .
Birdless Summer is an autobiography by Han Suyin .
The Wicked Years is a series of novels by Gregory Maguire that present a revisionist take on L. Frank Baum 's The Wonderful Wizard of Oz , its 1939 film adaptation , and related books .
De revolutionibus orbium coelestium ( On the Revolutions of the Heavenly Spheres ) is the seminal work on the heliocentric theory of the Renaissance astronomer Nicolaus Copernicus ( 1473 - -1543 ) .
Puttering About in a Small Land is an early non - science fiction novel by noted science fiction author Philip K. Dick .
The Hundred Secret Senses is a 1995 novel by Amy Tan , focusing on the relationship between Chinese - born Kwan and her younger , Chinese American sister Olivia , who serves as the book 's primary narrator .
Družba Pere Kvržice is a children 's novel written by Croatian children 's novelist Mato Lovrak .
Fafhrd and the Gray Mouser are two sword - and - sorcery heroes appearing in stories written by American author Fritz Leiber .
Craig 's Wife is a 1925 play written by American playwright George Kelly , uncle of actress and later Princess of Monaco Grace Kelly .
My Book about ME is a children 's book written but not illustrated by Theodor Geisel under the pen name Dr. Seuss and published by Random House on September 12 , 1969 .
Les Orientales is a collection of poems by Victor Hugo , inspired by the Greek War of Independence .
The Spell Compendium was compiled by Matthew Sernett , Jeff Grubb , and Mike McArtor , and was published in December 2005 .
The Chalk Garden is a play by Enid Bagnold that premiered on Broadway in 1955 .
Les Bravades is a 68-page picture book by Orson Welles , written and drawn in 1956 , and published posthumously in 1996 .
Troll Fell is a children 's fantasy novel written by Katherine Langrish , the first in the Troll Trilogy which comprises Troll Fell , Troll Mill and Troll Blood .
Who 'll Save Alfie Atkins ? ( Swedish : Vem räddar Alfons Åberg ? ) is a 1976 children 's book by Gunilla Bergström .
`` The Return of William Proxmire '' is a short story by Larry Niven first published in 1989 in the anthology What Might Have Been ?
The Last Colony is the third science fiction novel by John Scalzi set in the Old Man 's War universe .
Historia general de las Indias ( General History of the Indies ) is the account by Francisco López de Gómara of the Spanish conquest of the Aztec Empire .
Dracula is an 1897 Gothic horror novel by Irish author Bram Stoker .
The Constitution of the Athenians ( The Athenian constitution ; Greek : Ἀθηναίων πολιτεία Athenaion Politeia ) is the name given to two texts from Classical antiquity : one probably by Aristotle or a student of his , the second attributed to Xenophon , but not thought to be his work .
How to Make a Bird by Australian author Martine Murray is a children 's novel which centres on a young adolescent girl called Mannie .
Fielding Gray is Volume IV of the novel sequence Alms for Oblivion by Simon Raven , published in 1967 .
Vaskilintu ( Finnish : The Brass Bird or The Copper Bird or The Bronze Bird ) is a historical novel by Finnish author Kaari Utrio .
The Leopard ( Italian : Il Gattopardo ) is a novel by Giuseppe Tomasi di Lampedusa that chronicles the changes in Sicilian life and society during the Risorgimento .
Bog Child is a historical novel by Siobhan Dowd published by David Fickling in September 2008 , more than a year after her death .
Dime Store Magic is a fantasy novel by written by Kelley Armstrong .
Journeys to the End of the World ( 2007 ) is the debut novel by Clive Algar which is reviewed in the May 2009 issue of Historical Novels Review Online .
`` A Tale of the Ragged Mountains '' is a short story written by Edgar Allan Poe partially based on his experiences while a student at the University of Virginia .
Metro 2035 ( Russian : Метро 2035 ) is a post - apocalyptic science fiction novel by Russian author Dmitry Glukhovsky .
Fire Ice is the third book in the NUMA Files series of books co - written by best - selling author Clive Cussler and Paul Kemprecos , and was published in 2002 .
A Burnt - Out Case ( 1960 ) is a novel by English author Graham Greene , set in a leproserie on the upper reaches of a tributary of the Congo River in Africa .
`` The Haunter of the Dark '' is a horror short story written by H. P. Lovecraft in November 1935 , and published in the December 1936 edition of Weird Tales ( Vol . 28 , No . 5 , p. 538 - -53 ) .
French Silk is a romance novel written by Sandra Brown .
Joe Turner 's Come and Gone is a play by American playwright , August Wilson .
The Folk of the Faraway Tree is a children 's novel in the Faraway Tree series by Enid Blyton .
Hypnerotomachia Poliphili(/hiːpˌnɛəroʊtəˈmɑːkiːə pəˈliːfəˌliː/ ; from Greek hýpnos , ' sleep ' , éros , ' love ' , and máchē , ' fight ' ) , called in English Poliphilo 's Strife of Love in a Dream or The Dream of Poliphilus , is a romance said to be by Francesco Colonna and a famous example of early printing .
A Tolkien Miscellany is a collection of short stories , translations , and poetry written or translated by J. R. R. Tolkien , published by the Quality Paperback Book Club on January 1 , 2002 .
The Ginger Cat and Other Lost Plays is a collection of plays by Anglo - Irish fantasy writer Lord Dunsany , edited and with an introduction by Darrell Schweitzer .
Dik Trom is a series of Dutch children 's books by Cornelis Johannes Kieviet , centered on the character Dik Trom ( a mischievous oversized Dutch boy ) .
The Flies ( French : Les Mouches ) is a play by Jean - Paul Sartre , written in 1943 .
The Tartar Steppe ( Italian : Il deserto dei Tartari , literally The Desert of the Tartars ) is a novel by Italian author Dino Buzzati , published in 1940 .
Always Room for One More is a book by Sorche Nic Leodhas that won the Caldecott Medal for excellence in American children 's literature illustration in 1966 .
`` Auld Lang Syne '' ( Scots pronunciation : ( ˈɔːl(d ) lɑŋˈsəin ) : note `` s '' rather than `` z '' ) is a Scots poem written by Robert Burns in 1788 and set to the tune of a traditional folk song ( Roud # 6294 ) .
Tonguing the Zeitgeist is a Avantpop novel by Lance Olsen , published in 1994 by Permeable Press .
The Feast of the Goat ( Spanish : La fiesta del chivo , 2000 ) is a novel by the Peruvian Nobel Prize in Literature laureate Mario Vargas Llosa .
Family Catastrophe ( Chinese : 家變 ; pinyin : Jiābiàn ) is a novel by the Taiwan author Wang Wenxing published in 1972 .
De Interpretatione or On Interpretation ( Greek : Περὶ Ἑρμηνείας , Peri Hermeneias ) is the second text from Aristotle 's Organon and is among the earliest surviving philosophical works in the Western tradition to deal with the relationship between language and logic in a comprehensive , explicit , and formal way .

USS Albemarle ( 1863 ) was a screw steamer captured by the Union Navy during the American Civil War .

François Louis Dedon - Duclos ( 21 October 1762 -- 19 January 1830 ) was a French military commander of the Revolutionary Wars and the Napoleonic Wars .

Milton Montgomery ( May 3 , 1825 -- May 23 , 1897 ) was a colonel in the Union Army during the American Civil War who was nominated and confirmed for appointment to the grade of brevet brigadier general in 1866 .

Charles Garrison Harker ( December 2 , 1837 -- June 27 , 1864 ) was a brigadier general in the Union Army during the American Civil War .
Vittorio Ambrosio ( 28 July 1879 -- 19 November 1958 ) was an Italian general who served in the Italo - Turkish War , World War I , and World War II . During the latter conflict , Ambrosio served an instrumental role in the fall of Benito Mussolini and the eventual Italian renunciation of its alliance with Germany .
Albert Desbrisay Carter DSO & Bar ( 2 June 1892 -- 22 May 1919 ) was a Canadian World War I flying ace credited with 28 victories .

Rev. John G. Burkhalter , was a Baptist minister and highly decorated chaplain who served in World War II and the Korean War .

Alessandro Geraldini ( also Gerardini or Gueraldini)(1455 - -March 8 , 1524 ) was a Renaissance humanist scholar at the Spanish court of King Ferdinand and Queen Isabella .
Terwyn Davies ( born 3 April 1979 ) is a Welsh broadcaster , originally from Ceredigion in Wales , who is currently presenting S4C 's farming and rural affairs programme , Ffermio .
Manuel Guillermo Pinto ( 1783 -- June 28 , 1853 ) was an Argentine general and lawmaker .
Zhang Xunwei ( Chinese : 张迅伟 ; born 28 February 1989 in Liaoning ) is a Chinese football player who currently plays for Chinese Super League side Shanghai Shenxin .
Claude of France ( 13 October 1499 -- 20 July 1524 ) , daughter of Louis XII , inherited the Duchy of Brittany from her mother , Anne , and became Queen of France as the first wife of Francis I.
Brother Joche Albert Ly ( 8 February 1910 -- 21 April 1951 ) was a Chinese Marist Brother , and was martyred in Zhejiang , China by members of the People 's Liberation Army for denouncing Communism .
Nic Stene ( 25 May 1921 -- 20 May 2006 ) was a Norwegian speed skater , born in Trondheim .
James Hyman ( born 18 April 1970 ) is a DJ , Radio & TV presenter , Music Supervisor , MD of JLH ( creative media -- marketing company ) and founder of The Hyman Archive .
Alfredo Zalce Torres ( 12 January 1908 -- 19 January 2003 ) was a Mexican artist and contemporary of Diego Rivera , David Siqueiros and other better - known muralists .
Angela Adams ( born in 1965 on the island of North Haven , Maine ) is an American rug designer .
Giorgos Kyriakakis ( Greek : Γιώργος Κυριακάκης ) was born in 1967 in Crete where he took his first music lessons .
Rebecca Henderson ( born 27 September 1991 ) is an Australian mountain biker , specialising in cross country events .
Bekim Christensen ( born 17 September 1973 ) is a Danish retired professional road bicycle racer .
Miran Božovič ( born August 12 , 1957 ) is a Slovenian philosopher , associated with the Ljubljana school of psychoanalysis .
Thomas Pieters ( 27 January 1992 ) is a Belgian professional golfer who currently plays on the European Tour .
Wang Xiaotian ( simplified Chinese : = 王小天 ; traditional Chinese : 王小天 ; pinyin : Wāng Xiǎotiān ; born 26 August 1988 in China ) is a Chinese baseball infielder for the Jiangsu Hopestars .
Mike Grandmaison ( born 1954 ) is a Canadian nature photographer specializing in landscapes , plants and wildlife .
Henry Barratt born 28 April 1983 in Oxford , Oxfordshire , England is a rugby union player for the London Wasps in the Guinness Premiership .
Simon Grix ( born 28 September 1985 ) is an Irish international rugby league player for Warrington in the European Super League .
Joseph Brummer ( 1883 - 14 April 1947 ) was a Hungarian - born art dealer and collector who exhibited both antique artifacts from different cultures , early European art , and the works of modern painters and sculptors in his galleries in Paris and New York .
Proscovia Alengot Oromait ( born 1 January 1993 ) is a Ugandan university student and politician .
Turpal Tokaev ( born 20 November 1984 ) is Russian - Chechan - Kazakh - Turkish kickboxer and actor of Chechen descent .
Barbara Assoon ( born 1929 ) is a Trinidadian actress and journalist who has been one of her country 's public personalities for six decades .
Urta Rozenstruik ( born 20 May 1975 in Paramaribo ) is a Dutch bobsledder born in Suriname .
Bacho Kiro ( Bulgarian : Бачо Киро ) ( 7 July 1835 -- 28 May 1876 ) was the nickname of Kiro Petrov Zanev ( Киро Петров Занев ) , a Bulgarian teacher , man of letters and revolutionary who took an active part in the April Uprising .
Linda Geiser ( born 13 May 1935 ) is a Swiss film and television actress best known for her role in the Swiss TV series Lüthi und Blanc as Johanna Blanc .
Renato Adriano Jacó Moreira , or simply Renato Cajá , ( born 15 September 1984 ) is a Brazilian footballer who currently plays for Sharjah FC .
Rezaul Karim Hira ( Bengali : রেজাউল করিম হীরা ; born 1 December 1942 ) is a Bangladesh Awami League politician who has been the Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Jamalpur-5 since 1996 , and is chairman of the Parliamentary Standing Committee on the Ministry of Land .
Charles Johnson Maynard ( May 6 , 1845 -- October 15 , 1929 ) was an American naturalist and ornithologist born in Newton , Massachusetts .
Karel Destovnik , pen name and nom de guerre Kajuh ( Slovene convention : Karel Destovnik -- Kajuh , 19 December 1922 -- 22 February 1944 ) was a Slovenian poet , translator , resistance fighter , and Yugoslav people 's hero .
Kennedy Kimwetich ( born 1 January 1973 ) is a retired Kenyan middle distance runner who specialised in the 800 metres .
Peter Throckmorton ( 1928 -- June 5 , 1990 in Newcastle , Maine ) , was an American journalist and a pioneer underwater archaeologist , frequently described as the Father of Underwater Archaeology .
Jean Romaric Kevin Koffi ( born 25 June 1986 ) is an Ivorian footballer who under contract with the Belgian club Westerlo .
Mark Sunley ( born 13 October 1971 ) is a former footballer who made 37 appearances in the Football League playing as a centre back for Darlington and Hartlepool United .
Wikus du Toit ( born 18 June 1972 ) is a South African actor , comedian , composer , and director .
Carl Safina ( born 1955 ) is author of various books and many other writings about how the ocean is changing , lives of free - living animals , and the human relationship with the natural world .
Bill Liao ( born William Fu Wei Liao , 1967 ) is an Australian entrepreneur .
Grigorios Polychronidis ( born on 13 August 1981 in Batumi , Georgia ) is a Greek boccia player with a Paralympic boccia classification of BC3 .
Salvatore Capezio ( 1871 - -1940 ) was an Italian - born shoemaker who established Capezio , one of the world 's largest manufacturers of dance apparel and specialized dance shoes including ballet pointe shoes .
Harrie Gommans ( born 20 February 1983 ) is a Dutch professional footballer who plays as a striker for Spouwen - Mopertingen in the Belgian Promotion at the fourth level of Belgian football .
Kelsey - Lee Roberts ( born 20 September 1991 in East London , South Africa ) is an Australian athlete specialising in the javelin throw .
Michael Speechley ( born 29 April 1964 ) is an Australian former professional rugby league player for the Newtown Jets , the South Sydney Rabbitohs , the Cronulla Sharks and the Parramatta Eels .
Monsignor Patrick McKinney was born on 30 April 1954 , the eldest son of Irish immigrants Patrick and Bridget McKinney , and brought up in Birmingham .
William L. Reese ( born 1921 ) was a faculty member in the Department of Philosophy , State University of New York at Albany .
Sir Ferdinando Gorges ( July 1565 -- May 24 , 1647 ) , the `` Father of English Colonization in North America '' , was an early English colonial entrepreneur and founder of the Province of Maine in 1622 , although Gorges himself never set foot in the New World .
Helen Garner ( born 7 November 1942 ) is an Australian novelist , short - story writer , screenwriter and journalist .
Julian Lethbridge ( born 1947 ) is a British Ceylon - born , US - based , British abstract painter and drawer .
Sheena Blackhall ( b. Sheena Booth Middleton ) was born in 1947 in Aberdeen , daughter of the manager of Strachan 's Deeside Omnibus Service , Charles Middleton , and his second cousin , farmer 's daughter Winifred Booth .
Asad Qizilbash ( born 5 October 1963 ) is a Pakistani sarod player .
Abraham Woyna ( Wojna ; Lithuanian : Abraomas Voina ) ( 1569 - -1649 ) was a Roman Catholic priest and auxiliary bishop of Vilnius ( 1611 - -1626 ) , bishop of Samogitia ( 1626 - -1631 ) and then bishop of Vilnius ( 1631 - -1649 ) .
Kerry Kohansky Roberts ( born 1975 ) is an American film producer best known for her work on the 2008 film Nick and Norah 's Infinite Playlist .
Lee Radford ( born 26 March 1979 , in Kingston upon Hull ) is an English rugby league coach and former professional rugby league footballer who is currently head coach of Hull FC .
Shafqat Amanat Ali Khan ( Urdu : شفقت امانت علی‎ ; born 26 February 1965 ) is a Pakistani classical singer belonging to Patiala Gharana lineage .

Yu Lihua ( 於梨華 ) ( 1931 - ) is a Taiwanese - American woman writer .

Nadège Lacroix ( born 30 June 1986 ) is a Swiss actress , television personality .
Geoffrey Galt Harpham ( born 1946 ) is an American academic who until recently served as President and Director of the National Humanities Center .
Sir Hugh Montgomery , 1st Viscount Montgomery of the Great Ards ( c. 1560 -- 15 May 1636 ) was an aristocrat and a soldier , known as one of the `` founding fathers '' of the Ulster - Scots along with Sir James Hamilton , 1st Viscount Claneboye .
Aijaz Ali ( born 20 June 1968 ) is a Pakistani born American former cricketer .

Gavin Butt ( born 1967 ) is a British art historian based at Goldsmiths , University of London .
Alastair MacLennan ( born 1943 in Blair Atholl , Perthshire , Scotland ) is one of Britain 's major practitioners of live art . Since 1975 , he is based in Belfast , Northern Ireland .
Osama Alomar ( Arabic : اسامة الحويج العمر ) born Damascus , Syria , 1968 , is a Syrian short story writer poet and essayist .
W. Bobby Whiteley ( born 1871 in Wortley , Leeds -- death unknown ) was a rugby union footballer of the 1890s , playing at representative level for England , and at club level for Bramley , as a Forward , e.g. Front row , Lock , or Back row .
Juan Luis Martínez Martínez ( born 26 June 1972 ) is a Mexican politician affiliated to the National Regeneration Movement ( formerly to the Citizens ' Movement . He currently serves as Deputy of the LXII Legislature of the Mexican Congress representing Oaxaca .
Luis Candelaria ( 29 October 1892 - 23 December ) , was an Argentine Army officer and military aviator who was the first to cross the Andes by aeroplane , in April 1918 .

Sir Nicholas Dominic Cadbury ( born 12 May 1940 ) is a British businessman and member of the Cadbury chocolate manufacturing dynasty .

Elio Altramura ( died 2004 ) was an Italian art director .
Arthur Lee Loeb ( 13 July 1923 , Amsterdam - 19 July 2002 , Cambridge , Massachusetts ) was a Dutch scientist and crystallographer .
Ernst Stern ( 1 April 1876 -- 28 August 1954 ) was a German scenic designer that through his collaborations with most of the prominent German directors of the early Twentieth century helped define the look of Expressionism in both the theatre and the cinema .
František Jiránek ( 24 July 1698 -- 1778 ) was a Czech ( Bohemian ) Baroque composer , musician and very likely a student of Antonio Vivaldi .
Remo Bianco , birth name Remo Bianchi , ( 3 June 1922 -- 23 February 1988 ) was an Italian painter and sculptor .
Bleiddud was Bishop of St David 's ( then known as Menevia ) in Wales from 1061 to 1071 .
Phil Mellor ( Phil ' Mez ' Mellor , died 7 June , 1989 ) was a Yorkshire - based motorcycle racer .
François Xavier de Schwarz or François - Xavier - Nicolas Schwartz ( 8 January 1762 -- 9 October 1826 ) was born in Baden but joined the French army in 1776 .
Clement Coke ( died 24 May 1629 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1629 .
Guillemundus ( also Guillemó ) ( died 827 ) was count of Razès and Conflent , in what is now southern France .
Paolo Farinella ( 13 January 1953 -- 25 March 2000 ) was an Italian scientist very active in the planetary field and in the study of asteroids and small bodies of the Solar System .
Friedrich Wilhelm Schneidewin ( 6 June 1810 -- 11 January 1856 ) , was a German classical scholar .
Charles Delagrave ( 17 January 1881 -- 25 August 1952 ) was a Canadian notary and politician .
Józef Sylwester Sosnowski ( died 31 December 1783 ) , of the Nałęcz coat - of - arms , was a Polish - Lithuanian magnate --
King Robbo ( born John Robertson , 23 October 1969 -- 31 July 2014 ) was an English underground graffiti artist .
Squadron Leader Robert Anthony Maurice Palmer VC DFC * ( 7 July 1920 -- 23 December 1944 ) was an English posthumous recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious military decoration for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Nicholas Petanovich , born Nikola Petanović ( Serbian : Никола Петановић ) ( 1892 - 29 January 1932 ) , nicknamed `` Naiad '' , was an American Montenegrin emigrant , philosopher , writer , political publicist and fighter for Montenegro 's sovereignty and independence .
Richie Emselle ( 24 September 1917 - 16 January 1992 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Maurie Edwards ( 17 October 1922 -- 26 February 2007 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon and North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Evelyn Reed ( 1905 -- 1979 ) was an American communist and women 's rights activist .
James Eights ( 1798 - -1882 ) was an American physician , scientist , and artist .
Halina Szymańska ( 1906 - -1989 ) was a Polish spy , working for the British government , known as the Allies conduit to Nazi German Admiral Wilhelm Canaris .
Sir William Albert Jenkins ( 9 September 1878 -- 23 October 1968 ) was a Welsh coal exporter and ship owner and Liberal politician .
Cecilia Makiwane ( 1880 - -1919 ) was the first African registered professional nurse in South Africa and an early activist in the struggle for women 's rights .
John Boydell ( /ˈbɔɪdəl/ ; 19 January 1720 ( New Style ) -- 12 December 1804 ) was an 18th - century British publisher noted for his reproductions of engravings .
Paul Mondoloni ( September 27 , 1916 -- July 29 , 1985 ) , alias Monsieur Paul , was an important figure of the French Connection , who was killed in 1985 .
Marshall Ellison Smith , Sr . ( 21 November 1933 -- 14 May 1999 ) , was an American painter , sculptor and printmaker based in Alapaha , Ga.
Mihai Ivăncescu ( 22 March 1942 -- 2 January 2004 ) was a former Romanian football player .
Cuno Amiet ( 28 March 1868 -- 6 July 1961 ) was a Swiss painter , illustrator , graphic artist and sculptor .
Jacques Feyerick ( Ghent , 28 December 1874 - somewhere , 13 November 1955 ) was a Belgian athlete , who specialised in hurdling .
Charles Stanton Devas ( b. Woodside , Old Windsor , England , of Protestant parents , 26 August 1848 ; died 6 November 1906 ) was a political economist .
Mark Bullock ( 24 October 1872 -- 22 April 1925 ) was an English cricketer : a batsman who played four first - class matches for Worcestershire in 1900 .
Leslie Ballamy ( 1904 - 1991 ) was an inventor and automotive engineer who had a major impact on the British motorsport scene both before the Second World War and in the post - war period .
Begum Sufia Kamal ( Bengali : সুফিয়া কামাল ; 20 June 1911 -- 20 November 1999 ) was a Bangladeshi poet and political activist .
Nicolai A. Grevstad ( 2 June 1851 -- 20 February 1940 ) was an American diplomat , politician and newspaper editor .
Sonja Savić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Соња Савић ; 15 September 1961 -- 23 September 2008 ) was a cult Serbian actress , famous for her husky voice and series of impressive roles in some of the more memorable 1980s films made in former Yugoslavia .
Vilhelm Tveteraas ( 18 April 1898 -- 4 January 1972 ) was a Norwegian printmaker , painter and illustrator .
Jan Karol Chodkiewicz ( c. 1560 -- 24 September 1621 ; Belarusian : Ян Караль Хадкевіч , Jan Karal Chadkievič , Lithuanian : Jonas Karolis Chodkevičius ) was a military commander of the Polish--
Frederick Henry Piesse , CMG ( 6 December 1853 -- 29 June 1912 ) was a farmer , businessman and politician who is credited with much of the early development of the region around Katanning , Western Australia .
Thomas Wentworth , 1st Baron Wentworth and de jure 6th Baron le Despencer , PC ( 1501 -- 3 March 1551 ) was an English peer and courtier during the Tudor dynasty .
Sir John Garrard , sometimes spelt Gerrard ( c. 1546 -- 7 May 1625 ) , was a City of London merchant , a member of the Worshipful Company of Haberdashers , a Buckinghamshire landowner , and a Lord Mayor of London .
Ralph A. Tudor ( 1902 - 1962 ) was a builder , civil engineer and Under Secretary of the United States Interior Department .
Thomas New ( 1827 - -1914 ) was an early settler of the north west of New South Wales .
Grace Stoermer ( 1887 - -1961 ) was a Los Angeles civic leader , banking executive , and the first woman to serve as the Secretary of the California State Senate .
Antipope Eulalius ( died 423 ) was antipope from December 418 to April 419 , in opposition to Pope Boniface I. At first the claims of Eulalius as the rightful Pope were recognized by the Emperor Honorius , who sent a letter dated 3 January 419 recognizing him and pardoning the partisans of Boniface provided they left Rome .
Malcolm Archibald Macdonald ( June 20 . 1875 Lucknow , Ontario - October 1941 ) was a Canadian lawyer , politician and Chief Justice of British Columbia .
Samuel Hall Lord , also called `` Sam Lord '' ( 1778 -- 5 November 1844 ) was one of the most famous buccaneers on the island of Barbados .
George Bayntun ( 4 August 1873 - September 1940 ) was an English bookseller , bookbinder , and collector .
Henry Gabriel Ginaca ( May 19 , 1876 - 1918 ) was an American engineer who invented , at the direction of Hawaiian pineapple magnate James Dole in 1911 , a machine that could peel and core pineapples in an automated fashion .
Admiral Charles Middleton , 1st Baron Barham PC ( 14 October 1726 -- 17 June 1813 ) was a British naval officer and politician .
Thomas Dilward ( 1840 - -1902 ) , also known by the stage name Japanese Tommy , was an African - American dwarf who performed in the blackface minstrel show .
Elling Carlsen ( 8 September 1819 -- 18 April 1900 ) was a Norwegian skipper from Hammerfest and seal hunter , Elling Carlsen is credited with the 1871 discovery of Willem Barentsz ' 1596 winter stay on the north - eastern shore of Novaya Zemlya .
Trần Thái Tông ( birth name : Trần Cảnh , 17 July 1218 -- 4 May 1277 ) was the first emperor of the Trần Dynasty , seated on the throne for 33 years ( 1226 - -58 ) , being Grand Emperor for 19 years .
J .- Émile Ferron ( 25 September 1896 -- 2 March 1970 ) was a lawyer and federal Quebec politician .
Áed Findliath died on 20 November 879 , at Druim Inasclainn : in the territory of Conaille .
Queen Anu or Lady Anu ( Mongolian : Ану хатан ; also known as Ana Dara ; birth date unknown - 1696 ) was granddaughter of Ochirtu Secen Khan of Khoshuud ( or his youngest daughter according to some written historical sources ) , who was the nephew and adopted son of Güshi Khan .
Sir Arnold Ashley Miles CBE FRS ( 20 March 1904 -- 11 February 1988 ) , known as Ashley Miles , was the Director of the Lister Institute of Preventive Medicine and Professor of Experimental Pathology in the University of London from 1952 to 1971 .
Marchetto Cara ( c. 1470 -- probably 1525 ) was an Italian composer , lutenist and singer of the Renaissance .
Vera Rózsa OBE ( or Vera Rozsa - Nordell , Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈvera ˈroːʒa ) ) ( 16 May 1917 -- 15 October 2010 ) was a Hungarian singer , voice teacher , and vocal consultant .
Sapargali Begalin , born 24 November 1895 in Abralinsky and died 10 March 1983 , was a Kazakh poet .
Juan Lombía ( 1806 in Zaragoza -- 1851 in Madrid ) was a Spanish actor , author and theatre impresario .
Gertrude Aston Thimelby ( 1617 - -1668 ) was an English poet and author , who became a Roman Catholic nun late in life .
Mabel Fuller Blodgett ( 1869 - -1959 ) was a novelist and writer of children 's books .
Penny Dann ( 30 June 1964 -- 20 December 2014 ) was a British children 's book illustrator and creator of The Secret Fairy .
Olav Nordrå ( 25 December 1919 , Hammerfest - 28 April 1994 ) was a Norwegian writer .
Elleston Trevor ( 17 February 1920 -- 21 July 1995 ) was a British novelist and playwright who wrote under several pseudonyms .
Herbert Jenner ( born 23 February 1806 at Mayfair , London ; died 30 July 1904 at Falfield , Gloucestershire ) was an English barrister .
Buchanan Sharp ( 2 November 1894 -- 11 January 1956 ) was a Scottish professional footballer who played for Clydebank Juniors , Vale of Leven , Chelsea , Tottenham Hotspur , Leicester City , Nelson and Southport .
Captain John Allen , 4th Viscount Allen ( b. bef . 1726 -- 10 November 1753 ) was an Irish peer and politician .
Adegboyega Folaranmi Adedoyin ( 11 September 1922 -- January 2014 ) was a Nigerian - born British high jumper and long jumper .
Sydney Gedge ( 16 October 1829 -- 6 April 1923 ) was a British Conservative politician and prominent lay member of the Church of England .
Gerhard Charles Aalders ( 25 March 1880 -- 30 January 1961 ) , usually styled as G. Ch . Aalders , was a Dutch Old Testament scholar .
Stanley Woods ( 1903 -- 28 July 1993 ) was an Irish motorcycle racer famous for 29 motorcycle Grand Prix wins and winning the Isle of Man TT races 10 times in his career .
Tengku Ampuan Bariah Binti Al - Marhum Sultan Hisamuddin Alam Shah Al - Haj ( 31 August 1933 -- 21 March 2011 ) was the Tengku Ampuan Besar ( Queen ) of Terengganu from 1979 to 1998 as the wife of Sultan Mahmud Al - Muktafi Billah Shah .
Smith D. Woods ( December 2 , 1830 -- December 28 , 1888 ) was a Democrat Mayor of Kansas City in 1874 and 1875 .
Rudy Sternberg , Baron Plurenden Kt ( 17 April 1917 -- 5 January 1978 ) was an Austro - British industrialist and farmer .
Johann von Lamont FRSE , also referred to as Johann Lamont ( 13 December 1805 -- 6 August 1879 ) , was a Scottish - German astronomer and physicist .
Frederick G. Scheibler , Jr. ( 1872 - -1958 ) was an American architect .
Akatsuka Jitoku ( 1871 - 1936 ) was a Japanese artist .
Guy Buckingham ( 11 February 1921 -- 17 November 2015 ) was an English aircraft engineer who established the Australian automobile manufacturer `` Nota '' in 1952 in Oxford before taking it to Australia in 1955 .
Rev William Lucas Collins ( baptised 23 May 1815 -- 24 March 1887 ) was a Church of England presbyter and essayist .
Risteard Ó Foghludha ( 5 March 1871 - -20 August 1957 ) was an Irish - language teacher , journalist and editor from near Youghal , County Cork .
Egid Quirin Asam ( 1 September 1692 ( baptized ) - 29 April 1750 ) was a German plasterer and sculptor active during the period of the Late Baroque .
Wang Shifan ( 王師範 ) ( 874 -- July 10 , 908 ? ) was a warlord late in the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , who ruled Pinglu Circuit ( 平盧 , headquartered in modern Weifang , Shandong ) from 889 to 905 ( formally , as its military governor ( Jiedushi ) from 891 to 903 ) .
William George Verney ( 1871 - -1950 ) was a footballer who made six appearances as a half - back , scoring once , in the FA Cup for Southampton St. Mary 's between 1888 and 1896 .
Ernest A. Batchelder ( 1875 - -1957 ) was an American artist and educator who made Southern California his home in the early 20th century .
William Guglielmo Niederland ( 29 August 1904 - 30 July 1993 ) was a German - American psychoanalyst and a pioneer in the scholarly field of psychogeography .
Federico Henríquez y Carvajal ( Santo Domingo , 16 September 1848 - - ibidem , 4 February 1952 ) was a writer , journalist and teacher from the Dominican Republic .
William Joseph Corbet ( 12 December 1824 -- 1 December 1909 ) was an Irish nationalist politician and Member of Parliament ( MP ) for constituencies in County Wicklow for most of the period from 1880 to 1900 .
Léopold Renaudin ( 11 March 1749 -- 7 May 1795 ) was a French revolutionary sworn to the Revolutionary Tribunal .
Leo Kofler ( also known by the pseudonyms Stanislaw Warynski or Jules Dévérité ; 26 April 1907 -- 29 July 1995 ) was an Austrian - German Marxist sociologist .
Florence Nightingale David , also known as F. N. David ( 23 August 1909 -- 23 July 1993 ) was an English statistician , born in Ivington , Herefordshire , England .
Gregory Blaxland ( 17 June 1778 -- 1 January 1853 ) was an English pioneer farmer and explorer in Australia , noted especially for initiating and co - leading the first successful crossing of the Blue Mountains by European settlers .
Alice Harrison ( 1852 -- May 3 , 1896 ) was an English stage actress born in London .
Sir Herbert Smith , 1st Baronet ( 22 June 1872 -- 14 July 1943 ) , known as `` Piggy '' Smith , was an English carpet manufacturer .
Louis Campbell - Tipton ( 1877 - -1921 ) was an American composer ; a native of Chicago , Illinois , he was resident in Paris from 1901 .
Herb Friend ( 6 July 1888 -- 13 March 1954 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne and St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Daniel Priest ( 1814 - 1883 ) was a convict and bushranger in nineteenth century Tasmania .
Christopher Rolleston CMG , ( 27 July 1817 -- 9 April 1888 ) was an English - born colonial public servant in Australia .
William Goodhugh ( 1799?--1842 ) was an English bookseller and writer .
Ralph Robertson ( 31 August 1881 -- 11 May 1917 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) and had a noted career in New South Wales .
Goh Eng Wah ( 1923 -- 5 September 2015 ) was a film distributor , and one of the pioneers in Singapore 's cinema industry .
Otto Brusiin ( 1906 - 1973 ) was a leading Finnish teacher of law .
George Koriatovich , also known as George Korjatowicz or Jurg Korjat ( Polish : Jerzy Koriatowicz ) ( after 1330 -- 1375 - 1377 ) , was a Lithuanian prince , a member of the Gediminid dynasty .
John de Ros , 7th Baron de Ros of Helmsley ( c.1397 -- 22 March 1421 ) was an English nobleman .
Bogdan Bogdanović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Богдан Богдановић ; 20 August 1922 − 18 June 2010 ) was a Serbian architect , urbanist and essayist .
Lt . Philip Dalton ( 1903 - 25 July 1941 ) was a United States military scientist .
Philip of Aragon ( Spanish : Felipe de Aragón , Italian : Filippo d'Aragona ; 1449/50 - -1488 ) was the Archbishop of Palermo from 31 January 1477 , when he received confirmation of his election from Sixtus IV until he renounced his see in 1485 .
Di Biagio Baldassarre del Firenze ( 1430/1434 - -1484 ) was an Italian Renaissance painter .
Elizabeth Compton , Countess of Northampton ( 19 August 1694 -- 13 March 1741 ) , suo jure 14th Baroness Ferrers of Chartley , was a British peer .
Ilie Antonescu ( born 1894 , died 1974 ) was a Major General of the Romanian Armed Forces during World War II . He became a Commanding Officer 6th Calarasi Cavalry Regiment in 1941 , and moved to the 55th Exploration Group and then to the 6th Calarasi Cavalry Regiment that year .
Gertrud Kraus ( Hebrew : גרטרוד קראוס‎ ; 5 May 1901 - 13 November 1977 ) was an Israeli pioneer of modern dance in Israel .
Jean Carles ( 1892 - -1966 ) was a French perfumer who worked in Roure ( now part of Givaudan ) in the early 20th century .
Watkin Tench ( 6 October 1758 -- 7 May 1833 ) was a British marine officer who is best known for publishing two books describing his experiences in the First Fleet , which established the first settlement in Australia in 1788 .
Reg Owen ( 3 February 1921 -- 23 May 1978 ) was an English conductor and arranger .
John Weever ( 1576 - -1632 ) was an English antiquary and poet .
Áine Ní Cheanainn , headmistress and co - founder of Cumann Scannán na nÓg , 1907 - -1999 .
Maria Piotrowiczowa , a January insurgent , participant of the battle of Dobra ( the Łódź province ) , born in 1839 , killed on 24 February 1863 .
Luigi Lucchini ( 21 January 1919 -- 26 August 2013 ) was an Italian businessman and steel executive .
George Maniakes ( Greek : Γεώργιος Μανιάκης , transliterated as Georgios Maniaces , Maniakis , or Maniaches , Italian : Giorgio Maniace ) ( died 1043 ) was a prominent Byzantine Greek general during the 11th century , he was the catepan of Italy in 1042 .
Leonard Mann ( 15 November 1895 -- 29 April 1981 ) was an Australian poet , and novelist .
Ruaidhri Ó Cianáin ( died 1387 ) was an Irish historian .
Kazuaki Kimura ( 24 April 1946 -- 26 September 2015 ) was a professor and researcher of modern Japanese literature at Ritsumeikan University , Kyoto .
Niels Diffrient ( 6 September 1928 -- 8 June 2013 ) was an American industrial designer .
Pope Romanus ( died November 897 ) was Pope from August to November 897 .
Daniel Terry ( 1780?--1829 ) was an English actor and playwright , known also as a close associate of Sir Walter Scott .
Leofwine Godwinson ( c. 1035 -- 14 October 1066 ) was a younger brother of Harold II of England , the fifth son of Earl Godwin .
Gabino Sosa Benítez ( 1938 - -2003 ) was a Uruguayan comedian , itinerant singer , popular musician .
Grażyna Bacewicz ( Polish pronunciation : ( ɡraˈʐɨna baˈt͡sɛvit͡ʂ ) ; 5 February 1909 -- 17 January 1969 ) was a Polish composer and violinist .
Hendrick van Buyten ( 1632 - July 1701 ) was a baker in Delft .
Ian Buchan ( c.1920 - 1965 ) was manager of Everton Football Club from 1956 to 1958 .
Sir Peter Riddel ( died 18 April 1641 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1624 and 1640 .
William Cawthra ( 29 October 1801 -- 26 October 1880 ) was a philanthropist , business and civic leader and the eldest son of Joseph Cawthra .
Christine Sadler ( 1902 - -1983 ) , born in Silver Point , Putnam County , Tennessee , was an American author , journalist , and magazine editor .
Karl Holdhaus ( 21 January 1883 , in Baden bei Wien -- 30 June 1975 ) was an Austrian entomologist who specialised in Coleoptera .
Johannes Emil Gnudtzmann ( 17 November 1837 -- 14 April 1922 ) was a Danish architect working in the Historicist style .
Yuchi Gong ( 585 - -658 ) , courtesy name Jingde , better known as Yuchi Jingde , posthumously known as Duke Zhongwu of E , was a Chinese general who lived in the early Tang dynasty .
Stanisław Ledóchowski ( 1666 - -1725 ) was a polish marshal of the Crown Tribunal ( 1701 ) , member of the Sandomierz Confederation of 1704 , marshal of the Tarnogród Confederation ( 1715 - -1716 ) , marshal of the Sejm during Sejm Niemy of 1717 .
Abdur Rouf Choudhury ( 1929 - -1996 ) was a Bengali writer Choudhury was born on 1 March 1929 , in Habiganj District , Bangladesh ( then part of Assam ) where his father Azhar Choudhury , a land owner , and his mother Nazmun Nesa Choudhury , a house wife resided .
Danny Lui ( Lui Tam Ping ) ( 7 January 1957 - 1 July 2012 ) was a Hong Kong entrepreneur and venture capitalist .
Asa Eldridge ( 1809 -- 1856 ) was a sea captain from Yarmouth , Massachusetts .
Sammy Ofer ( born Samuel Herskovich ; 22 February 1922 -- 3 June 2011 ) was an Israeli shipping magnate and philanthropist .
Asllan Rusi ( 4 October 1944 - -1983 ) is a former Albanian volleyball player who played for Dinamo Tirana and the Albanian national team .
Luis Carrillo was , from November 1567 to about July 1568 , royal commissioner with Alonso Muñoz for the inspection of the viceregal government of New Spain for King Philip II .
Daphne Pollard ( 19 October 1892 in Fitzroy , Melbourne -- 22 February 1978 in Los Angeles ) was an Australian actress in American films , mostly short comedies .
Helen Lessore OBE ( 31 October 1907 -- 6 May 1994 ) was a gallerist and the director of the Beaux Arts Gallery in London as well as an English modernist painter and visual artist .
Polyclès Langlois ( 29 September 1814 -- 30 November 1872 ) was a French writer , draughtsman and painter .
Enrique Santos Discépolo ( Discepolín ) ( 27 March 1901 -- 23 December 1951 ) was an Argentine tango and milonga musician and composer , author of famous tangos such as `` Cambalache '' and many others performed by several of the most important singers of his time , amongst them notably Carlos Gardel .
Julian Sleigh , ( 6 October 1927 in Florence - 2 October 2013 in Cape Town ) was a Christian Community priest , councillor , founding member of Camphill in South Africa and author .
Sir Edward Ward , 1st Baronet of Bexley ( c. 1618 - -1684 ) was twice Sheriff of Norfolk in 1655 - -56 and 1656 - -57 .
Congalach mac Conaing Cuirre ( died 696 ) was a King of Brega from the Uí Chonaing sept of the Síl nÁedo Sláine branch of the southern Uí Néill .
Sir Bryan Stapleton KG ( c. 1322 -- 1394 ) was an English medieval knight from Yorkshire .
James H. Brookes , D. D. ( 27 February 1830 -- 18 April 1897 ) , American religious writer , was pastor of Walnut Street Presbyterian Church in St. Louis , Missouri .
Joseph Caulfield James ( 6 July 1860 -- 6 July 1925 ) was an English teacher from Birkenhead , England .
Camille Decreus , sometimes written as Camille DeCreus or Camille de Creus ( 23 September 1876 -- 26 September 1939 ) was a French composer and pianist .
Luigi Gaspare Peyri or Louis Gaspard Balthazar Pierre Léon Marie Peyri ( 1758 -- 1822 ) became a general officer in the army of the Kingdom of Italy which was a satellite of Napoleon 's First French Empire .
Harold A. Reid ( also known by the pen name H. Reid ) ( 1925 - -1992 ) was an American writer , photographer , and historian .
Henry Clay Lewis ( 1825 - -1850 ) was an American short story writer and medical doctor from the middle of the 19th century .
Ilse - Margret Vogel ( 5 June 1914 -- 7 October 2001 ) was a German - American author who mostly wrote for children and young adults .
Sir Thomas Moyle ( born before 1500 - died 2 October 1560 , probably at Eastwell , Kent ) was a commissioner for Henry VIII in the dissolution of the monasteries , and speaker of the House of Commons in the Parliament of England from 1542 to 1544 .
Vuča Žikić ( Serbian Cyrillic : Вуча Жикић , mid-18th century -- 14 April 1808 ) , known as Captain Žika , was an important figure in the First Serbian Uprising .
Raimondo della Torre ( died 23 February 1299 ) was an Italian clergyman , who was patriarch of Aquileia from 1273 until his death .
Janice H. Levin ( 1913 - -2001 ) was an American philanthropist and art collector from New York City .
William Chatterton ( 27 December 1861 -- 19 March 1913 ) was an English cricketer and footballer .
Shi Jingtang ( 石敬瑭 ) ( 30 March 892 -- 28 July 942 ) , also known by his temple name Gaozu ( 高祖 ) , was the founding emperor of imperial China 's short - lived Later Jin during the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period , reigning from 936 until his death .
Major - General Sir Stuart Greeves KBE CB DSO and Bar , MC and Bar ( 1897 - -1989 ) was a British Indian Army officer .
Jacques - François Ochard ( 1800 - -1870 ) was a French artist , remembered as the first art teacher of Claude Monet at his high school .
Herman Bicknell ( 2 April 1830 -- 14 March 1875 ) was an FRAS , British surgeon , orientalist , and linguist , son of Elhanan Bicknell .
Noel George Williams ( 19 September 1943 -- 5 January 2015 ) , better known as King Sporty , was a Jamaican DJ , reggae musician , and record producer for the Tashamba and Konduko labels .
Sarah Crompton ( 1802 -- 13 May 1881 ) was an English children 's writer .
Paul Thümmel ( 15 January 1902 -- 20 April 1945 ) , aka Agent A-54 , was a German double agent who spied for Czechoslovakia during World War II . He was a high - ranking member of the German military intelligence organisation , the Abwehr , who was also a highly decorated Nazi party member .
Liu Gongquan ( simplified Chinese : 柳公权 ; traditional Chinese : 柳公權 ; pinyin : Liǔ Gōngquán ; Wade -- Giles : Liu Kungch'üan ) ( 778 - -865 ) , courtesy name Chengxuan ( 诚悬 ) , was a Chinese calligrapher who stood with Yan Zhenqing as the two great masters of late Tang calligraphy .
Peter Hersleb Classen , frequently also P. H. Classen , ( 10 March 1738 --19 May 1825 ) was a Danish - Norwegian statesman and director of Det Classenske Fideicommis .
Hanna Hammarström ( Stockholm , 4 November 1829 - 1909 ) , was a Swedish inventor and industrialist .
Georgios Remoundos ( Γεώργιος Ρεμούνδος , 1878 , Athens -- 27 April 1928 ) was a Greek mathematician and a founding member of the Academy of Athens in 1926 .
James Thomas Molesworth ( 1795 -- 13 July 1871 ) was a military officer in the services of the British East India Company , and one of the most prominent lexicographers of the Marathi language .
Thomas Percival Lancaster ( ca 1877 -- 1968 ) was a newspaper publisher and political figure in Ontario .
Dr. Edward Keonjian ( 14 August 1909 -- 6 September 1999 ) was a prominent engineer , an early leader in the field of low - power electronics , the father of microelectronics .
Salomon II ( Ge'ez ሣሎሞን ) was nəgusä nägäst ( 13 April 1777 -- 20 July 1779 ) of Ethiopia .
Robert Porrett ( 1783 - -1868 ) was an English amateur chemist and antiquary .
Albert Glotzer ( 1908 - -1999 ) , also known as Albert Gates was a professional stenographer and founder of the Trotskyist movement in the United States .
Saira Elizabeth Luiza Shah , née Elizabeth Louise MacKenzie , ( 1900 -- 15 August 1960 ) was a Scottish writer who wrote under the pen name Morag Murray Abdullah .
Major John Leslie Charles ( 1892 - 1992 ) was Chief Engineer for the Canadian National Railway ( Western Region ) and consulting engineer for the Canadian National Railway .
Princess Katarzyna Lubomirska ( died 1611 ) was a Polish szlachcianka .
August Ludwig Schott ( 1751 - -1787 ) was a German lawyer and professor .
Jean - Baptiste Dumouchelle ( Dumouchel ) ( 5 April 1784 -- 29 March 1844 ) was born in Sandwich ( now Windsor ) , Upper Canada .
Brunhilde Sonntag ( 27 September 1936 -- 18 December 2002 ) was a German composer , musicologist and music teacher .
Georges Baal ( born György Balassa ; 17 May 1938 -- 6 December 2013 ) was a Hungarian writer , theatrologist , actor , director and psychologist .
Archibald Meston ( 26 March 1851 -- 11 March 1924 ) was an Australian politician , civil servant , journalist , naturalist and explorer .
Gubbi Veeranna ( Kannada : ಗುಬ್ಬಿ ವೀರಣ್ಣ ; 1890 -- 1974 ) was an Indian theatre director , one of the pioneers and most prolific contributors to Kannada theatre .
Esther Ballestrino ( 20 January 1918 -- disappeared 17 or 18 December 1977 ) was a Uruguayan martyr .
John Heaver DD ( d. 23 June 1670 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1662 - 1670
Maria Moninckx ( 22 April 1673 ( baptised ) - 26 February 1757 ( buried ) ) was a Dutch botanical artist and painter , best known for the colour plates she and her father , Jan Moninckx , created and which make up the nine - volume Moninckx Atlas .
Theodor Rosebury ( London , 10 August 1904 - -Conway , Massachusetts , 25 November 1976 ) was a British - born American bacteriologist and author .
Norm Betson ( 8 July 1914 -- 5 May 1988 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the early 1940s .
Matt Devlin ( 30 April 1950 -- 28 December 2005 ) was a Provisional Irish Republican Army volunteer who took part in the 1981 Irish hunger strike and was later a leading member of Sinn Féin in County Westmeath , Republic of Ireland .
Uzi Feinerman ( Hebrew : עוזי פיינרמן‎ , born 1924 , died 8 April 1975 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Alignment between 1969 and 1975 .
Ferenc Szombathelyi ( né Knausz or Knauz ; 17 May 1887 - 4 November 1946 ) was a Hungarian military officer who served as Chief of Army Staff during World War II .
Richard Yarward or Yearwood ( 1580 - -1632 ) was an English grocer and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1629 .
Abda of Hira ( died 680 ) was a monk of the Assyrian Church of the East .
Silahdar Damat Ali Pasha ( 1667 -- 5 August 1716 ) , also called Silahdar Ali Pasha , was an Ottoman general and Grand Vizier .
James Franklin Record ( June 21 , 1861 -- 1935 ) was a pastor , school teacher , and President of Pikeville Collegiate Institute , and later Pikeville College .
Mac Ahlberg ( 12 June 1931 -- 26 October 2012 ) was a Swedish film director and cinematographer .
Lorenzo Lauri ( 15 October 1864 -- 8 October 1941 ) was an Italian Cardinal of the Catholic Church who served as Major Penitentiary from 1927 and Camerlengo from 1939 until his death and was elevated to the cardinalate in 1926 .
Bernard Peiffer ( pie - fer ) ( 23 October 1922 -- 7 September 1976 ) was a French jazz pianist , composer , and teacher .
James ( Jack ) Cummins ( 1773 - -1849 ) was a Texas farmer , public official and a colonist of Stephen F. Austin 's first settlement in Texas .
Janus of Cyprus ( 1375 -- 29 June 1432 ) was a King of Cyprus , King of Armenia and a Titular King of Jerusalem from 1398 to 1432 .
Sancho Alfónsez ( or Adefónsez ) ( ca . 1093 -- 29 May 1108 ) was the only son of Alfonso VI of Castile and León and his heir from May 1107 , eventually co - ruling from Toledo .
Harold Shukman ( 23 March 1931 -- 11 July 2012 ) was a British historian , specializing in the history of Russia .
Karl August Devrient ( 5 April 1797 -- 3 August 1872 ) was a German stage actor best known for performances of Schiller and Shakespeare .
Zalmon Libin , usually known as Z. Libin ( 1872 - 1955 ; real name : Yisrael - Zalman Hurvits or Gurvitz ) , was a writer of short stories and a playwright in Yiddish theater , active around 1900 .
Wilhelm Josef Oomens SJ ( 14 September 1918 -- 27 June 2008 ) was a Dutch Jesuit and painter .
Vincent Melzac ( 1914 - -1989 ) was an American business executive and art collector , best known as one of the earliest and most daring collectors of paintings of the Washington Color School .
Dinu Lipatti ( Romanian pronunciation : ( ˈdinu liˈpati ) ; 1 April ( O.S. 19 March ) 1917 -- 2 December 1950 ) was a Romanian classical pianist and composer whose career was cut short by his death from causes related to Hodgkin 's disease at age 33 .
Pieter Christoffel Wonder ( 10 January 1780 , Utrecht - 12 July 1852 , Amsterdam ) was a Dutch painter , active in England .
Maraimalai Adigal ( 15 July 1876 -- 15 September 1950 ) was an eminent Tamil orator and writer .
Ciriaco Ceballos Neto or Ciriaco Cevallos y Bustillo ( Quijano , Cantabria , 1763 - México , 1816 ) was a Spanish sailor , explorer and cartographer .
Thomas Harrison Burder ( 1789 - -1843 ) was an English physician and author .
Henry James Wilson Scherren ( 10 February 1843 -- 25 April 1911 ) , usually known as Henry Scherren or in encyclopaedia articles as H. Sc .
Janet Elliott Wulsin ( 1894 - -1963 ) was an early 20th - century explorer , whose accomplishments place her in line with contemporary women explorers such as Alexandra David - Neel .

Joey Hawthorne ( Died 1980 ) lived in the Las Vegas Valley and was a professional poker player and writer who contributed the section on lowball poker to Doyle Brunson 's Super / System .
John Quincy Adams Nadenbousch ( 31 October 1824 -- 13 September 1892 ) was a successful businessman , soldier and local politician .
Liam Weldon ( 15 October 1933 - 28 November 1995 ) was a singer and songwriter in the Irish folk tradition .
Lieutenant Colonel William Roy Hodgson CMG OBE ( 22 May 1892 -- 24 January 1958 ) was an Australian soldier , public servant and diplomat .
Sado Khan died in 1626 leaving five sons , from whom have descended several well - known clans of the Durrani tribe .
Abu'l - Husain Abd - Allah ibn Ahmad Utbi , better known as Abu'l - Husain Utbi ( died November 982 ) , was an Iranian statesman from the Utbi family , who served as the vizier of the Samanid ruler Nuh II from 977 to 982 .
Rabbi Samuel Buchler ( March 21 , 1882 -- April 1971 ) , was the President of the Federation of Hungarian Jews in America , in 1909 in New York .
Sir Robert Gore - Booth , 4th Baronet ( 25 August 1805 -- 21 December 1876 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician and landowner , who built Lissadell House , located in County Sligo .
Philip O'Sullivan Beare ( Irish : Pilib Ó Súilleabháin Béirre , c. 1590 ; died in Spain , 1660 ) was an Irish soldier who became more famous as a writer .
David Heinz Gumbel ( 1906 - -1992 ) was an Israeli designer and silversmith , born in Germany .
Major - General John Soame Richardson ( 16 March 1836 -- 9 June 1896 ) , C.B. , was a British army officer and Commander of the Forces in colonial New South Wales .
Felix Ehrenhaft ( 24 April 1879 -- 4 March 1952 ) was an Austrian physicist who contributed to atomic physics , to the measurement of electrical charges and to the optical properties of metal colloids .
Kola Beldy ( Russian : Кола́ Бельды́ ) ( 2 May 1929 -- 21 December 1993 ) was a Soviet pop singer of Nanai ethnicity .
Alexander MacDonnell , 3rd Earl of Antrim ( 1615 -- 10 December 1699 ) was a Roman Catholic peer and military commander in Ireland .
The Master of the Saint Bartholomew Altarpiece ( sometimes called the Master of the Saint Bartholomew Altar , ) was an Early Netherlandish painter active in Germany between 1475/1480 and 1510 .
William Theilheimer ( 1914 -- 14 July 2005 ) , who was born in Augsburg , Germany , played a significant role in the history of what is now known as chemoinformatics .
Eugene C. Keyes ( August 23 , 1900 - 1963 ) was a Lieutenant Governor in the US state of Michigan from 1943 - -45 and again from 1947 - 49 .
Bernard Verdcourt ( 20 January 1925 -- 25 October 2011 ) was a biologist and taxonomist , most widely known as a botanist and latterly an Honorary Research Fellow at the Royal Botanic Gardens , Kew in London .
