Elfrida De Renne Barrow ( 1884 - -1970 ) was an author and poet who has been honored as a Georgia Woman of Achievement .
Charles Marsham , 1st Earl of Romney ( 28 September 1744 -- 1 March 1811 ) , known as The Lord Romney between 1793 and 1801 , was a British politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1768 to 1790 , inherited his peerage in 1793 and was created Earl of Romney in 1801 .
John Ashwell ( died 1541 ) , was the prior of Newnham Abbey , in Bedfordshire .
Henry William Henfrey ( 1852 - -1881 ) was an English numismatist .
John Majhor ( 28 November 1953 -- 23 January 2007 ) was a radio and television host , most noted for his work in Toronto , Canada .
Joan Ambrosio Dalza ( fl . 1508 ) was an Italian lutenist and composer .
Else Meidner ( born Else Meyer ; 2 September 1901 -- 7 May 1987 ) was a German - Jewish painter .
Ludwig Franz Alexander Winther ( 9 March 1812 -- 26 April 1871 ) was a German pathologist and ophthalmologist who was a native of Offenbach am Main .
Commander Sir Arthur Trevor Dawson , 1st Baronet ( 1 May 1866 -- 19 May 1931 ) was an English businessman who served as managing director of the armaments giant Vickers from 1906 to 1931 .
Thomas Bartholomew Curran ( 1870 -- 1929 ) was an Irish barrister and an Anti - Parnellite / Irish National Federation politician who served in the United Kingdom House of Commons as Member of Parliament ( MP ) for the constituencies of Kilkenny City ( 1892 - -1895 ) and North Donegal ( 1895 - -1900 ) .
Mandel Szkolnikoff ( 1895 - 1945 ) better known as Michel Szkolnikoff , was a Russian businessman .
Tsuji Gettan Sukemochi ( 辻月丹資茂 ) ( sometimes read as Shukeshige ) ( 1648 - 1728 ) was a Japanese swordsman who founded the kenjutsu of Mugai - ryū in 1695 .
Ľudmila Pajdušáková ( 29 June 1916 -- 6 October 1979 ) was a Slovak astronomer .
Joan Ramis ( 27 April 1746 -- 12 February 1819 ) was a historian from Minorca , lawyer and writer .
Lieutenant Henry Boswell Bennett ( 1809 -- 1838 ) of the 45th Regiment of Foot ( Sherwood Foresters ) became on 31 May 1838 the first officer to die in the service of Queen Victoria when he was shot by John Nichols Thom in Bossenden Wood in Kent .
Thomas Emerson Forster ( 20 October 1802 -- 7 March 1875 ) was an eminent English mining engineer .
Willi Bars ( 13 February 1916 - January 2000 ) is a former German footballer .
Lieutenant - Colonel Thomas Frederic Tweed MC ( 1890 - -30 April 1940 ) was a British soldier and novelist .
Sheffield Airey Neave CMG OBE ( 20 April 1879 - 31 December 1961 ) was a British naturalist and entomologist .
Shujauddin Butt ( 10 April 1930 -- 7 February 2006 ) was a Pakistani army officer and cricketer who played in 19 Tests from 1954 to 1962 .
Bartholomew Booth ( c. 1732 - 1786 ) was a pioneer in American education .
Henry Farnham Perkins ( 1877 - -1956 ) was an American zoologist and eugenicist .
Oakley C. Johnson ( 1890 - 1976 ? ) was an American socialist political activist and writer .
David Bogue ( 18 February 1750 -- 25 October 1825 ) was a British nonconformist leader .
Bishop Chu Chi Zui ( born in 1923 in China - died 1990 ) , he studied for the Priesthood of the Roman Catholic Church after completing university studies in law .
Beatrice of Brandenburg ( Polish : Beatrycze Brandenburska , German : Beatrix von Brandenburg ; ca . 1270 -- bef . 26 April 1316 ) , was a German princess and a member of the House of Ascania in the Brandenburg branch .
George Ponsonby PC ( 5 March 1755 -- 8 July 1817 ) , was a British lawyer and Whig politician .
Maria van Beckum ( before 1510 -- 13 November 1544 ) was a Dutch noblewoman and Anabaptist executed for heresy .
Sir Patrick Reilly , GCMG ( 17 March 1909 -- 6 October 1999 ) was a British diplomat who served as ambassador to the USSR and France .
Sir Reginald James Neville Neville , 1st Baronet ( 22 February 1863 -- 28 April 1950 ) , born Reginald Neville White , was a British barrister and Conservative and Unionist member of parliament .
Gerallt Lloyd Owen ( 6 November 1944 -- 15 July 2014 ) was a Welsh - language poet , considered one of the best `` strict metre poets '' in Wales .
Alexander van Bredael ( 1 April 1663 -- 14 July 1720 ) was a Flemish painter known for Italianate landscapes and genre scenes of fairs , cattle markets and villages .
Toyan aka Ranking Toyan ( born Byron Letts , died 1991 ) was a Jamaican reggae deejay active since the mid-1970s and best known for his early 1980s recordings .
Sheheke , Sheheke - shote , translated as White Coyote , and also known as Coyote or Big White ( 1766 - -1812 ) , was a Mandan chief .
Jordi Estadella ( 11 November 1948 -- 30 April 2010 ) was a Spanish voice actor , journalist , radio and television host and film dubber .
Marta Eggerth ( 17 April 1912 -- 26 December 2013 ) was a Hungarian - born American actress and singer from `` The Silver Age of Operetta '' .
Sheikh Mohammad Rohani(1220 - 1305 AD)(Pashto:شيخ محمد روحانى ) also known as Shah Mohammad Rohani and Rohani Ba Ba was a Sufi cleric born around 1220 AD .
Tetlepanquetzal ( died 1525 ) was a Mexican king , He was the fourth Tepanec king of Tlacopan , and reigned after 1503 as a tributary of the Mexican emperor Moctezuma II , whom he assisted in the first defence of Mexico .
John Woodcock Graves ( 9 February 1795 -- 17 August 1886 ) was a composer and author of `` D'ye ken John Peel '' .
Caterina Visconti ( 1361 -- 17 October 1404 ) was a member of the Italian noble family Visconti , which ruled Milan from 1277 to 1447 .
Adrian Hastings ( 23 June 1929 -- 30 May 2001 ) was a Roman Catholic priest , historian and author .
Antonio Signorini ( 2 April 1888 -- 23 February 1963 ) was an influential Italian mathematical physicist and civil engineer of the 20th century .
Luís Gonçalves das Chagas , Baron of Candiota ( c.1815 - 1894 ) was a Brazilian landowner , military leader and noble .
Thora Maria Fredrika Hildegard Björck ( 1 May 1847 -- 7 April 1920 ) was the first Swedish woman to complete an academic degree .
Lalla ( c. 720 - -790 CE ) was an Indian mathematician , astronomer , and astrologer who belonged to a family of astronomers .
Arthur Dolphin ( 24 December 1885 -- 23 October 1942 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who kept wicket for Yorkshire County Cricket Club between 1905 and 1927 .
Frederick Flowers ( 1810 - -1886 ) was a police magistrate .
Richard Tracy ( died 1569 ) was an English lay Protestant reformer .
Coloman of Galicia - Lodomeria ( Hungarian : Kálmán , Ukrainian : Коломан ) ( 1208 -- 1241 ) was a member of the Árpád dynasty .
Thomas Crouch ( 1607 -- August 1679 ) was an English academic and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1679 .
Sir ( Laurence ) Dudley Stamp , CBE , DSc , D. Litt , LLD , Ekon D , DSc Nat ( 9 March 1898 -- 8 August 1966 ) , was professor of geography at Rangoon and London , and one of the internationally best known British geographers of the 20th century .

Richard MacGillivray Dawkins FBA ( 24 October 1871 -- 4 May 1955 ) was a British archaeologist .
Blessed Jeong Yak - jong ( 1760 -- 8 April 1801 ) , also known as Augustine Chong , was a Korean Roman Catholic martyr who contributed greatly to the spread of Roman Catholicism in Korea .
Yi Eon - jeok ( 1491 - -1553 ) , sometimes known by his pen name Hoejae , was a public official and intellectual of the middle Joseon Dynasty of Korea .
Helena M. Weiss ( 1909 - -2004 ) was an American museum administrator and registrar .
Dolly Nampijinpa Daniels ( 1936 - 2004 ) was an Australian Aboriginal ritual leader , Warlipiri speaker , renowned artist , and land -rights advocate for the Warlipiri people of the Northern Territory .
Walter F. Clayton ( 1865 in Boston , Massachusetts - 9 May 1942 in Greenport , Long Island , New York ) was an American architect , builder , and politician from New York .
Alberto Cassano ( 23 January 1935 -- 12 July 2014 ) was an Argentine engineer and academic .
Antonio Francisco Xavier Alvares ( Alvares Mar Julius , Julius Mar Alvarez ) ( 29 April 1836 -- 23 September 1923 ) was initially a priest in the Roman Catholic Church in Goa .
James P. Wilmot ( 1911 - -1980 ) was a pioneer aviation executive , landowner , philanthropist and horse breeder who served as Finance Chairman of the Democratic National Committee .
Arisztid Dessewffy ( Hungarian pronunciation : ( ˈɒristid deʒøːfi ) ; 2 July 1802 in Csákány / Čakanovce -- 6 October 1849 in Arad ) was a honvéd general in the Hungarian Army .
Franz I , Prince of Liechtenstein , born Franz de Paula Maria Karl August ( 28 August 1853 -- 25 July 1938 ) , was the Prince of Liechtenstein between 1929 and 1938 .
Frederick Weekes ( 1833 - 1920 ) was an English painter and designer .

Christian Ulrich ( 27 April 1836 - 22 January 1909 ) , was an Austrian - Hungarian architect .

Calbhach Ó Domhnaill , anglicized Calvagh O'Donnell ( died 1566 ) , eldest son of Manus O'Donnell , was an Irish King of Tyrconnell of the mid-16th century .
Jin Gyeong - suk ( June 24 , 1980 -- 2005 ) , also known as Jin Kyung - sook , was a North Korean woman who , after successfully defecting to South Korea in 2002 , was abducted in China two years later and forcefully deported back to North Korea , where she was tortured to death .
William Joscelyn Arkell MA , D Phil , D Sc , FGS , FRS ( 9 June 1904 -- 18 April 1958 ) was a British geologist and palaeontologist , regarded as the leading authority on the Jurassic Period during the middle part of the 20th century .
Marit Trætteberg , née Krogstad ( 28 September 1930 -- 27 October 2009 ) was a Norwegian chemist .
Shirley Firth ( 31 December 1953 in Aklavik , Northwest Territories -- 30 April 2013 ) was a Canadian cross - country skier who competed in the Winter Olympics in 1972 , 1976 , 1980 and 1984 .
William Corlett ( 8 October 1938 -- 16 August 2005 ) , was an English author , best known for his quartet of children 's novels , The Magician 's House , published between 1990 and 1992 .
Alvin Wood ( 1831 - -1891 ) was an early settler in the area that is now the north central part of Jefferson County , Kentucky .
Alfred Donald Trounson OAM ( 30 September 1905 -- 29 January 2009 ) was a British diplomat and amateur photographer who settled in Australia in his retirement to become a bird photographer and the founder of the National Photographic Index of Australian Wildlife .
György Sztantics ( Serbo - Croatian : Đuro Stantić ) ( Szabadka , 19 August 1878 -- Szabadka , 10 July 1918 ) was a Hungarian athlete ( ethnic Bunjevac from today 's Serbia ) who competed mainly in the 3000 metre walk .
John Chambre ( also Chamber or Chambers ) ( 1470 - -1549 ) was an English churchman , academic and physician .
Eric I , Duke of Brunswick - Grubenhagen nicknamed the winner ( German : Erich I. , Herzog von Braunschweig - Grubenhagen ; c. 1383 -- 28 May 1427 ) , ruled the Principality of Grubenhagen , a part of the Duchy of Brunswick - Lüneburg .
Herbert Snook ( 23 December 1867 -- 1947 ) was an English footballer who played in The Football League for Notts County .
Modeste Carlier ( 1820 - -1878 ) was a Belgian portrait and subject painter .
P.M. Sreenivasan ( 1919 - 1983 ) , who adopted the name Silpi , was a Tamil illustrator , best known for his detailed renditions of Tamil architecture and sculpture in Ananda Vikatan magazine .
Lionel Hastie ( 5 June 1911 - 9 April 1981 ) was an Australian rules footballer , who played for the Fitzroy Football Club in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Brother Leo ( died c. 1270 ) was the favorite disciple , secretary and confessor of St Francis of Assisi .
Dorothy J. Killam ( 1900 -- 26 July 1965 ) was an American - born Canadian philanthropist .
Lena Larsson , née Rabenius ( 31 July 1919 -- 4 April 2000 ) , was a Swedish interior designer , known as a pioneer for the unconventional , family - friendly environments she created , and for the 1960s modern wear - and - tear ideal .
Nikos Foskolos ( Greek : Νίκος Φώσκολος ; 26 November 1927 -- 30 October 2013 ) was a Greek screenwriter and director .
Henry Farren ( 1826?--1860 ) , was an English actor known mostly in comedy .
Guillaume de Littera ( 1371 - -1452 ) was a French Roman Catholic canon and provost in Aix - en - Provence as well as vicar in a diocese encompassing several localities in Provence .
Wenman Joseph Bassett - Lowke ( 27 December 1877 Northampton -- 21 October 1953 ) was the son of Joseph Tom Lowke , a Northampton boilermaker and his wife , Eliza , and is noted for having founded the firm of Bassett - Lowke which specialised in producing construction sets , and model railways , boats and ships .
Adnan Kapau Gani ( 16 September 1905 -- 23 December 1968 ) , often abbreviated as A. K. Gani , was an Indonesian politician .
Master I. A. M. of Zwolle ( known works 1470 - -1490 , lifetime estimated as ca . 1440 - -1504 ) was an anonymous Dutch goldsmith and engraver who signed many of his works with his initials I. A. M. or I. A. , and added `` Zwolle '' to some .
Jane Herbert Wilkinson Long ( 1798 - -1880 ) was a Texas pioneer .
Sir Charles Flower , 1st Baronet ( 1763 -- 1834 ) was a merchant who served as Lord Mayor of London in 1808 .
Ahmad Hussein Adl ( 1889 - -1962 ) was the minister of agriculture for several periods in the Ahmad Qavam , Ebrahim Hakimi , and Ebrahim Hakimi governments .
Liana Alexandra ( born Liana Moraru , 27 May 1947 -- 10 January 2011 ) was a Romanian composer , pianist and music educator .
Sir Guylford Slingsby ( 1565 - -1631 ) was an administrator who went on to be Comptroller of the Navy ; he produced a number of distinguished sons .
Robert Monson ( by 1532 -- 23 September 1583 ) was an English politician and judge .
Clark Tibbitts ( 1903 - 1985 ) was a gerontologist who helped bring attention to the topic of aging and establish programs for aging populations in the United States .
Charles Gordon , 11th Marquess of Huntly PC , DL , JP ( 5 March 1847 -- 20 February 1937 ) , styled Lord Strathavon until 1853 and Earl of Aboyne between 1853 and 1863 , was a Scottish Liberal politician .
Mariano Necochea ( born in Buenos Aires , 7 September 1790 ; died in Miraflores , near Lima , in 1849 ) was an Argentine - Peruvian soldier .
Christopher Erle ( c. 1590 -- 1634 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1621 and 1629 .
Julia Margaret Guerin Halloran Lavender ( 23 April 1858 in Williamstown , Victoria -- 26 July 1923 in Adelaide , South Australia ) , known popularly as Bella Guerin , was an Australian feminist , women 's activist women 's suffragist , anti - conscriptionist , political activist and schoolteacher .
Mary Honywood or Mary Waters ( 1527 -- 1620 ) was a British co - heiress who visited the Marian martyrs .
Annette Frances Braun ( 1884 - -1978 ) was an American entomologist and leading authority on microlepidoptera , the order that includes the smaller butterflies and moths .
Sir Robert Laurie Morant ( 7 April 1863 -- 13 March 1920 ) was an English administrator and educationalist
J. T. Adams ( July 17 , 1926 -- September 1993 ) was an American gospel singer , musician , record label founder and dramatist , the creator of Worthy Is the Lamb .
René Highway ( 1954 - -1990 ) was an Aboriginal dancer and actor of Cree descent from Brochet , Manitoba .
Yehuda Cohen ( Hebrew : יהודה כהן‎ ; ‎23 January 1914 -- 8 August 2009 ) was an Israeli judge .
Sofoklis Dousmanis ( Greek : Σοφοκλής Δούσμανης , 25 December 1868 -- 6 January 1952 ) was a Greek naval officer .
Percy Cudlipp ( 10 November 1905 -- 5 November 1962 ) , was a prominent Welsh journalist .
General of the Army Raden Soedirman ( Perfected Spelling : Sudirman ; 24 January 1916 -- 29 January 1950 ) was a high - ranking Indonesian military officer during the Indonesian National Revolution .
Claude Friese - Greene ( 3 May 1898 in Fulham , London -- 1943 in Islington , London ) was a British - born cinema technician , filmmaker , and cinematographer , most famous for his 1926 collection of films entitled The Open Road .
Sir William Maurice ( April 1552 -- August 1622 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1593 and 1611 .
Edwin Eden ( 21 April 1893 -- 25 October 1939 ) was an English cricketer who played two first - class matches in the early 1920s , one for Gloucestershire in 1921 , and the second nearly two years later for Worcestershire ( which county he had played against for Gloucestershire ) .
Peter de Alcobasse ( died 1427 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1422 to 1427 and Physician .
William Cropper ( 27 December 1862 -- 13 January 1889 ) was an English cricketer and football player who played cricket for Derbyshire CCC between 1882 and 1888 and football once for Derby County .
Henry de Vere Vane , 9th Baron Barnard FSA , JP , Hon . DCL ( 10 May 1854 -- 28 December 1918 ) was a British peer and Senior Freemason .
Séamus P. Ó Mórdha ( 8 October 1915 -- 12 February 2005 ) was an Irish teacher and historian .
António das Chagas , O.F.M. ( Anthony of the Holy Wounds ) , ( 25 June 1631 -- 20 October 1682 ) was a Portuguese Franciscan friar and ascetical writer .
David Robilliard ( 1952 - -1988 ) was a British poet and contemporary artist .
Robert de la Piere ( died 1258 ) was a trouvère of the so - called `` school '' of Arras .
Rembert Dodoens ( 29 June 1517 -- 10 March 1585 ) was a Flemish physician and botanist , also known under his Latinized name Rembertus Dodonaeus .
Teofil Fabiny ( 11 October 1822 - 4 March 1908 ) was a Hungarian politician and jurist , who served as Minister of Justice between 1886 and 1889 .
Giovanni Pietro Berti ( c. 1590 - -1638 ) was an Italian composer and organist of Saint Mark 's , Venice .
Robert Treat Paine , Jr. ( October 28 , 1835-August 11 , 1910 ) was a Boston lawyer , philanthropist and social reformer and great grandson of the signer of the Declaration of Independence .
Swami Madhavananda left his mortal body on Wednesday , 6 October 1965 at the age of 76 years 10 months .
Peter Copley ( 20 May 1915 -- 7 October 2008 ) was an English television , film and stage actor .
Charles Pickering Bowditch ( 30 September 1842 -- 1 June 1921 ) was an American financier , archaeologist , cryptographer and linguistics scholar who specialized in Mayan epigraphy .
Magnolia Thunderpussy ( 30 October 1939 -- 15 May 1996 ) , born Patricia Donna Mallon was a San Francisco burlesque performer , radio personality , filmmaker and restaurateur .
André Tiraqueau ( Latin : Andreas Tiraquellus ) ( 1488 - -1558 ) was a French jurist and politician .
Arnaud de Borchgrave ( 26 October 1926 -- 15 February 2015 ) was an American journalist who specialized in international politics .
Johann Wolfgang Döbereiner ( 13 December 1780 -- 24 March 1849 ) was a German chemist who is best known for work that foreshadowed the periodic law for the chemical elements .
Geoffrey Crawley ( 10 December 1926 -- 29 October 2010 ) was a photographic expert and journalist , and was the editor in chief of British Journal of Photography for two decades .
Samuel Selwyn Chamberlain ( 1851 - -1916 ) , American journalist and newspaper editor .
Neil Leslie Webster ( 7 November 1906 -- 1990 ) was an army Major who worked in intelligence in World War II . He was a key figure in radio intelligence and cryptography who worked in the Fusion Room at Bletchley Park and was closely involved in the hunt for `` cribs '' for the Enigma machine .
Vic Maile ( 1943 -- 1989 ) was a British record producer .
Miss Enid Lapthorn ( 23 July 1889 -- 18 November 1967 ) , was a British Liberal Party and later Liberal National politician .
José Antonio Roméu ( 1742 ? -- 1792 ) was sixth Spanish governor of Alta California , from 1791 to 1792 .
Albertus Parisiensis ( fl . 1146 -- 1177 ) , also known as Albert of Paris , was a French cantor and composer .
Sharda Bhargava ( 1912 - -1999 ) was a leader of Indian National Congress and a member of Rajya Sabha from Rajasthan .
Andreas Matzbacher ( 7 January 1982 -- 24 December 2007 ) was an Austrian professional road bicycle racer .
Ticasuk Brown ( 1904 - -1982 ) was an Iñupiaq educator , poet and writer .
Ronald Campbell Gunn , FRS , ( 4 April 1808 -- 13 March 1881 ) was a South African - born Australian botanist and politician .
Arthur Reed Ropes ( 23 December 1859 -- 11 September 1933 ) , better known under the pseudonym Adrian Ross , was a prolific writer of lyrics , contributing songs to more than sixty British musical comedies in the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
William Henry Bell , known largely by his initials , W H Bell ( 20 August 1873 -- 13 April 1946 ) , was an English composer , conductor and lecturer .
Samuel Holberry ( 18 November 1814 -- 21 June 1842 ) was a prominent Chartist activist .
David Scott Daniell ( 1 July 1906 -- 29 August 1965 ) , was an English author , historian and journalist .
The Most Reverend George Thomas Plunkett ( ? --8 May 1827 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic clergyman who served as the Bishop of Elphin from 1814 to 1827 .
Frank Chacksfield ( 9 May 1914 -- 9 June 1995 ) was an English pianist , organist , composer and conductor of popular light orchestral easy listening music , who had great success in Britain and internationally in the 1950s and early 1960s .
Hugh van Cutsem ( 21 July 1941 -- 2 September 2013 ) was an English landowner , banker , businessman , and horse - breeder .
Major George Henry Benton Fletcher ( 22 October 1866 -- 31 December 1944 ) was a collector of early keyboard instruments including virginals , clavichords , harpsichords , spinets and early pianos .
Stuart Olof Agrell ( 5 March 1913 -- 29 January 1996 ) was an outstanding optical mineralogist and pioneer collaborator applying the electron microprobe to petrology .
Sir Anthony Bateman ( died 1687 ) was an English merchant who was Lord Mayor of London in 1663 .
Kate McNiven ( died 1715 ) , also called Kate Nevin was a young nurse who served the House of Inchbrakie in the Parish of Monzie , near Crieff in Scotland in the early 1700s .
Olof Strömstierna ( 1664 - -1730 ) was a Swedish naval officer and admiral .
Eugeniu Voinescu ( commonly Eugen ; 26 May 1842 , Iași - 6 May 1909 , Bucharest ) was a Romanian diplomat and painter , who specialized in maritime scenes .
Norman James Brian Plomley , also known as Brian Plomley , ( born 6 November 1912 -- 8 April 1994 ) regarded by some as one of the most respected and scholarly of Australian historians and , until his death , in Launceston , the doyen of Tasmanian Aboriginal scholarship .
Pedro Campaña ( 1503 - -1586 ) was a Flemish painter of the Renaissance period , mainly active in Italy and Spain .
William Atwood ( c.1650 - 1712 ) was an English lawyer , known also as a political and historical writer .
Chen Shuozhen ( Chinese : 陳碩真 ; pinyin : Chén Shuòzhēn ; died 653 ) was a Tang dynasty woman from Muzhou ( in modern Chun'an , Zhejiang ) , who led a peasant uprising in 653 .
Austin Andrew Wright ( 4 June 1911 , Chester -- 22 February 1997 , Upper Poppleton , York ) was a British sculptor and teacher .
Matthew Raper ( 1705 - -1778 ) was a British astronomer , mathematician , and scholar in various fields .
Marián Filc ( 16 September 1948 -- 9 February 1993 ) was a Slovak figure skater who competed for Czechoslovakia .
Leon Yehuda Recanati ( 1890 - 1945 ) was a Greek - born businessman and Jewish community leader who became a prominent banker and philanthropist in Palestine .
Rechung Dorje Drakpa ( Wylie : ras chung rdo rje grags pa , 1083/4 - 1161 ) , known as Rechungpa , was one of the two most important students of the 11th century yogi and poet Milarepa and founder of the now - defunct Rechung lineage of the Kagyu school of Tibetan Buddhism .
Carl William Hansen ( 11 October 1872 -- 3 August 1936 ) was a Danish author , Luciferian , Wandering Bishop and Occultist .
Francis John Marnham ( 1853 - 1941 ) was a British Liberal politician and businessman .
( Robert John ) Douglas Gageby ( 29 September 1918 -- 24 June 2004 ) was the pre - eminent Irish newspaper editor of his generation .
Lord Charles Spencer - Churchill ( 3 December 1794 -- 28 April 1840 ) was a British nobleman , the second son of George Spencer - Churchill , 5th Duke of Marlborough .
Violet Brunton ( 1878 -- 1951 ) was an English artist educated at the Liverpool School of Art , where she studied woodcarving , miniature painting and book illustration .
Dame Jane Frances Dove , DBE , JP ( 27 June 1847 -- 21 June 1942 ) was an English women 's campaigner , who founded Wycombe Abbey and other girls ' schools .
James Barry Hutchinson ( 27 January 1936 -- 12 June 2005 ) , known as Barry Hutchinson , was an English professional footballer who scored 116 goals from 367 appearances in the Football League playing for Chesterfield , Derby County , Lincoln City , Darlington , Halifax Town and Rochdale .
Pier Maria III de ' Rossi ( 1504 -- 15 August 1547 ) was an Italian general and nobleman , the second marquess and seventh count of San Secondo .
Edmund Distin Maddick ( 1857 - -1939 ) was an English surgeon and pioneer of cinema .
Francis Garden , Lord Gardenstone ( 24 June 1721 -- 22 July 1793 ) was a Scottish lawyer and judge .
Jones Orin York ( August 5 , 1893 -- July 1970 ) was recruited in California by Soviet spy Stanislau Shumovskij approximately in 1935 .
Isaac Bloch ( 1848 - -1925 ) served as Chief Rabbi in Nancy , France .
Siegfred Karl Kast ( c. 1916 -- 1 December 1955 ) was a German immigrant to Australia who shot dead two doctors and unsuccessfully attempted to detonate a bomb in Wickham Terrace , Brisbane , before committing suicide .
Yehuda Arazi ( Hebrew : יהודה ארזי‎ ; 1907 - -1959 ) , code name Alon , was an Israeli who was active in the Haganah in Palestine during the British Mandate era .
Ryu Jagwang(korean:류자광 , hanja:柳子光 , 1439 -- June 1512 ) was a Korean Joseon Dynastys politician , soldier and writer .
Murshid Quli Khan , also known as Mohammad Hadi was the first Nawab of Bengal , serving in the post from 1717 to 30 June 1727 .
Enrico Silvestri ( b. May 12 , 1896 -- d. 1977 ) was an Italian Alpini officer and skier .
Columba McVeigh ( 1958 - 1 November 1975 ) was a man from Northern Ireland who was abducted and killed by the Provisional Irish Republican Army ( IRA ) .
Cemile Sultan ( 18 August 1843 -- 7 February 1915 ) was an Ottoman princess , daughter of Sultan Abdülmecid I and his wife Düzdidil Hanımefendi , the daughter of Şıhım Bey Dişan .
Dawlat Berdi ( died 1432 ) , also known as Devlet Berdi , was a Khan of the Golden Horde who reigned from 1419 to 1421 , and again from 1428 to his death in 1432 .
Nicolai Schejtli ( 24 June 1753 -- 4 April 1824 ) was a Norwegian mining official and politician .
Martin Farquhar Tupper ( 17 July 1810 , London -- November 1889 , Albury , Surrey ) was an English writer , and poet , and the author of Proverbial Philosophy .
William Henry Crump ( 17 April 1865 -- 14 January 1942 ) , better known by the stage name Harry Champion , was an English music hall composer , singer and Cockney comedian , whose onstage persona appealed chiefly to the working class communities of East London .
Henry Clifton Sorby ( 10 May 1826 - 9 March 1908 ) , was an English microscopist and geologist .
Guy Fawkes ( /ˈɡaɪ ˈfɔːks/ ; 13 April 1570 -- 31 January 1606 ) , also known as Guido Fawkes , the name he adopted while fighting for the Spanish , was a member of a group of provincial English Catholics who planned the failed Gunpowder Plot of 1605 .
Sir William James Fitzgerald ( May 1894 -- July 1989 ) was an Irish jurist who served as Chief Justice of the Supreme Court of Palestine during the time of the British Mandate .
Angus Daniel Campbell ( March 19 , 1884 -- March 5 , 1976 ) was the founder of the Northern Ontario Hockey Association ( NOHA ) , an executive member of the Ontario Hockey Association ( OHA ) and a member of the Hockey Hall of Fame .
William Honnyng ( 1520 - -1569 ) was an English Member of Parliament and Tudor Court official who served as Clerk of the Signet and Clerk of the Privy Council under Henry VIII and Edward VI .
Trịnh Tạc ( Hán : 鄭柞 ; 1606 - 1682 ) ruled Vietnam from 1654 - -1682 Trịnh Tạc was one of the most successful of the Trịnh lords who ruled northern Vietnam .
Alpheus Sherwin Cody ( November 30 , 1868 -- April 4 , 1959 ) was an American writer and entrepreneur who developed a long - running home - study course in speaking and writing and a signature series of advertisements asking `` Do You Make These Mistakes in English ? ''
William M. Kramer ( 1920 - 2004 ) was an American rabbi , university professor and art collector .
Thomas Francis McNamara , RIAI , RIBA , ( 1867 - -1947 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic ecclesiastical architect active throughout the late - nineteenth- to the mid - twentieth - century Ireland who designed many hospitals and Roman Catholic churches .
Jérémie Jacques Oberlin ( 8 August 1735 -- 10 October 1806 ) was an Alsatian philologist and archaeologist .
Giles of Santarém ( Gil ) ( about 1185 -- 14 May 1265 ) was a Portuguese Dominican scholar .
Hugh Price Hughes ( 9 February 1847 -- 17 November 1902 ) was a Welsh Christian clergyman and religious reformer in the Methodist tradition .
John Churchill Dunn ( 4 March 1934 -- 27 November 2004 ) , professionally known simply as `` John Dunn '' , was a disc jockey and radio presenter who worked for many years on BBC Radio .
George H. Richmond ( 1944 - -2004 ) was an American educator who introduced the concept of the MicroSociety to American primary education .
Daniel Lovell ( died 1818 ) was an English journalist , involved in high - profile court cases concerned with press freedom .
Johannes Thesselius ( Erfurt ca . 1590 -- Szeben , 1643 ) was a German - Transylvanian composer of church and dance music .
Kennedy Thomson ( 4 April 1936 -- May 1996 ) was a continuity announcer and presenter for Grampian Television .
Arthur Malcolm Trustram Eve , 1st Baron Silsoe GBE , MC , TD , KC ( 8 April 1894 -- 3 December 1976 ) , known as Sir Malcolm Trustram Eve , 1st Baronet , from 1943 to 1963 , was a British barrister and First Church Estates Commissioner .
Leicester Silk Buckingham ( 1825 - -1867 ) was an English dramatist , who achieved considerable popularity as a playwright , several of his free adaptations of French comedies being produced in London between 1860 and 1867 .
Hassan I of Morocco ( Arabic : الحسن الأول‎ ) ( 1836 -- 7 June 1894 ) was Sultan of Morocco from 1873 to 1894 .
Hema Upadhyay and her lawyer Haresh Bhambani were killed on Friday , 11 December 2015 , reportedly over a financial dispute .
Charles Webster Leadbeater ( /ˈlɛdˌbɛtər/ ; 16 February 1854 -- 1 March 1934 ) was an influential member of the Theosophical Society , author on occult subjects and co - initiator with J. I. Wedgwood of the Liberal Catholic Church .
Shamsiah Fakeh ( 1924 -- 20 October 2008 ) was a Malaysian nationalist and feminist .
Linghu Yu ( died 249 ) was an official of the state of Cao Wei during the Three Kingdoms period .
Mary Wright Sewell ( /ˈsuːəl/ ; 6 April 1797 -- 10 June 1884 ) was an English poet and children 's author .
Alexander Hardinge Patrick Hore - Ruthven ( 30 August 1913 -- 24 December 1942 ) was a British soldier and poet .
Caroline Pratt ( 23 June 1962 -- 4 September 2004 ) was a well - known rider in the equestrian discipline of three - day eventing .
Guido Terrena ( c.1270 in Perpignan -- 1342 ) , also known as Guido Terreni and Guy de Perpignan , was a Catalan Carmelite canon lawyer and scholastic philosopher .
Jeanne Mammen ( 21 November 1890 -- 22 April 1976 ) was a German painter and illustrator of the Weimar period .
Sir George Burrard , 3rd Baronet GCB GCMG ( 6 April 1769 -- 17 May 1856 ) was a Church of England priest .
Thomas Erskine , 9th Earl of Kellie ( about 1746 -- 6 February 1828 ) was a Scottish merchant , landowner and politician who for many years lived in the Swedish port city of Gothenburg .
Edward Jakobowski ( 17 April 1856 -- 29 April 1929 ) was an English composer , especially of musical theatre , best known for writing the hit comic opera Erminie .
King Daoxiang of Zhao ( Traditional Chinese : 趙悼襄王 ) ( died 236 BCE , reigned 244 BCE -- 236 BCE ) reigned in the State of Zhao during the Warring States period of Chinese history .
Count Lajos Széchényi de Sárvár - Felsővidék ( German : Ludwig Graf Széchényi von Sárvár und Felsövidék ; 28 March 1868 -- 14 April 1919 ) was an Austro - Hungarian diplomat of Hungarian origin serving as envoy to Bulgaria and the Netherlands during World War I.
Major - General Frederick Joseph Loftus - Tottenham , CBE , DSO and Bar ( born 1898 ; died 1987 ) was a British Indian Army officer during World War I and World War II .
Sir Tatton Sykes , 4th Baronet ( 1772 - -1863 ) was an English landowner and stock breeder , known as a patron of horse racing .
The Reverend George William Lemon ( 1726 -- 4 October 1797 ) was the author of an early etymological dictionary of the English language , published in 1783 .
John Debrett ( d. 1822 ) was an English publisher and compiler .
Wilbur Henry Siebert ( 30 August 1866 Columbus , Ohio -- 2 September 1961 Columbus ) was an educator and historian from the United States .
Bahrudin Čengić ( 7 January 1931 -- 16 October 2007 ) , sometimes credited as Bato Čengić , was a Bosnian screenwriter and film director who was active in Yugoslavia .
Ludwig Pollak ( 14 September 1868 , Prague -- 1943 , Auschwitz concentration camp ) was an Austro - Czech classical archaeologist , antiquities dealer , and director of the Museo Barracco di Scultura Antica in Rome .
Sir Ralph de Hengham ( 1235 -- 18 May 1311 ) was an English justice .
Alfred Hoare Powell ( 1865 - -1960 ) was an English Arts and Crafts architect , and designer and painter of pottery .
Francis Winthrop Palfrey ( 1831 - -1889 ) was an American historian , born in Boston , Massachusetts son of J. G. Palfrey .
James M. Baley , Jr. ( 1912 - 2003 ) was a North Carolina lawyer and judge .
Thumal the Qahraman ( Arabic : ثمل القهرمانة‎ ) ( died 929 ) was a Muslim woman appointed in 918 as a judge in a maẓālim ( secular administrative ) court .
Aart den Boer ( 30 December 1852 in Nieuw - Lekkerland -- 11 May 1941 ) was a Dutch architect and contractor .
Bernard Bolingbroke Woodward ( 1816 - -1869 ) was an English nonconformist minister , antiquarian , and Royal Librarian at Windsor Castle .
Richard Herst ( Hurst ) ( died 29 August 1628 ) was an English Roman Catholic recusant layman .
General Sir William Payne - Gallwey , 1st Baronet ( 1759 -- 16 April 1831 ) was a British soldier and Governor of the Leeward Islands .
Sir John Spelman ( 1594 - -1643 ) was an English historian and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1626 .
David Gervan McMillan ( 26 February 1904 -- 20 February 1951 ) , known as Gervan McMillan , was a New Zealand politician of the Labour Party , and a medical practitioner .
Ralph Hammond Innes ( 15 July 1913 -- 10 June 1998 ) was a British novelist who wrote over 30 novels , as well as children 's and travel books .
Cecil Weld - Forester , 1st Baron Forester ( baptised 7 April 1767 -- 23 May 1828 ) was a Tory British Member of Parliament and later peer .
Becić became a member of the Croatian Academy of Sciences and Arts in 1934 , at that time called the Yugoslav Academy of Sciences and Art . Vladimir Becić died in Zagreb 24 May 1954 .
Alexander Macbain ( or Alexander MacBain ) ( 22 July 1855 -- 4 April 1907 ) was a Scottish philologist , best known today for An Etymological Dictionary of the Gaelic Language ( 1896 ) .

Aeneas William Mackintosh ( 7 September 1819 -- 18 June 1900 ) was a Scottish Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1868 to 1874 .

Joan Canning , 1st Viscountess Canning ( née Scott ; 1776 -- 14 March 1837 ) was the wife of British Prime Minister George Canning .
George Alfred Grant , popularly known as Paa Grant ( 15 August 1878 -- 30 October 1956 ) , was a merchant and politician in the Gold Coast who has been called `` the father of Gold Coast politics '' .
Antonio Gramusset ( 1740 - -1784 ) was a French adventurer living in Chile , and one of the co - conspirators in the Conspiracy of the Tres Antonios .
Albrecht von Haller ( 16 October 1708 -- 12 December 1777 ) was a Swiss anatomist , physiologist , naturalist and poet .
Thomas Atkins Wardell ( ca . 1865 - -1902 ) was an Ontario lawyer and political figure .
Albert Joseph Pénot ( 1862 - -1930 ) was a French painter known for female nudes .
Matthew Rowan ( died April , 1760 ) was the acting colonial governor of North Carolina in 1753 and 1754 , following the death of governor Nathaniel Rice .
Martin Lindauer ( December 19 , 1918 -- November 13 , 2008 ) was a German behavioral scientist .
Henry Latham Currey ( 1863 -- 1945 ) , also known as Harry Currey was a British politician in the Cape Colony .
Melchor Ocampo ( 5 January 1814 , Maravatío , Michoacán -- 3 June 1861 , Tepeji del Río , Hidalgo ) was a Mexican lawyer , scientist , and liberal politician .
Bedřich Bloudek left the Austrian Army as lieutenant colonel and died on 11 August 1875 in the spa resort Toplice Topusko near Glina , Croatia .
Frederick Irby , 2nd Baron Boston ( 1749 - -1825 ) was an English aristocrat and courtier .
Michael Lvovitch Tsetlin ( the surname is also written Cetlin , Tzetlin , Zeitlin , Zetlin ; cyrillic : Михаил Львович Цетлин ) ( 22 September 1924 -- 30 May 1966 ) was a Russian mathematician and physicist who worked on cybernetics .
Mary E. Sawyer ( 1846 - 1902 ) , better known as Mollie Monroe , was an American old west woman who was known for crossdressing and for her liaisons with multiple men , among other things .
Peter Hasslacher ( 14 August 1810 -- 5 July 1876 ) was a German Roman Catholic preacher .
Boes Boestami ( Perfected Spelling : Bus Bustami ; 30 December 1922 -- 11 September 1970 ) was an Indonesian journalist and film actor .
Hugh Auchincloss Steers ( b. 1962 -- March 1 , 1995 ) was a painter whose work is in the Whitney Museum of American Art , the Walker Art Center , and the Denver Art Museum .
Frank Atha Westbury ( 5 May 1838 -- 24 September 1901 ) , who wrote under the pen names of `` Atha '' and `` Atha Westbury '' , was a popular and prolific author of mystery adventure novels , children 's stories and poetry in late 19th century Australia and New Zealand .
Bernard Barton ( 1784 - -1849 ) was known as the Quaker poet .

Barney Lazarus ( 18 December 1879 -- 6 May 1962 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Kenneth Athol Webster ( 17 December 1906 -- 5 October 1967 ) was a collector and dealer of manuscripts , fine art and ethnographic artifacts associated with Oceanic peoples .
Tom Gentleman FSIA ( 1892 - -1966 ) was a Scottish painter and commercial artist .
Father Francisco Ayerra de Santa María ( 1630 - -1708 ) is considered to be Puerto Rico 's first native born poet .

William Justice Ford ( 7 November 1853 -- 3 April 1904 ) was an English schoolmaster , known as a cricketer and sports writer .
Alexander Thomson ( 9 March 1873 -- 18 November 1953 ) , known as Alec Thomson , was an Australian politician , and a member of the Western Australian Legislative Assembly from 1914 until 1930 representing the seat of Katanning , and a member of the Western Australian Legislative Council representing the South Province from 1931 until 1950 .

Edwin Hamilton Davis ( 22 January 1811 in Ross County , Ohio -- 15 May 1888 in New York City ) was an American archaeologist and physician who completed pioneering investigations of the mound relics in the Mississippi Valley .
Professor Garth Chapman ( 8 October 1917 - -1 November 2003 ) was an academic and author in the field of zoology .
Dave Line ( 1942 -- 1980 ) was a British beer author .
Robert Cyril Layton Perkins FRS ( 15 November 1866 -- 29 September 1955 ) was a distinguished British entomologist , ornithologist , and naturalist noted for his work on the fauna of the islands of Hawaii and on Hymenoptera .
Miles Evergood ( 10 January 1871 -- 3 January 1939 ) was an Australian artist who achieved renown in Europe and the United States , as well as his native country .
James Culliford ( 8 September 1927 -- March 2002 ) was a British actor on stage , film and television .
William Proctor Swaby FRGS ( 1844 - -16 November 1916 ) was a colonial Anglican bishop from 1893 until 1916 .
Nicole Grasset ( July 1927 -- 29 August 2009 ) was a Swiss - French medical virologist and microbiologist - epidemiologist .
The Rev. William Keble Martin ( 9 July 1877 , Radley -- 26 November 1969 , Woodbury ) was a British priest , botanist and botanical illustrator , known for his Concise British Flora in Colour .
Anna Zawadzka ( 8 February 1919 , Warsaw - 22 June 2004 , Warsaw ) was a Polish teacher , author of textbooks , Scoutmaster ( harcmistrzyni ) , sister of Tadeusz `` Zośka '' Zawadzki and daughter of professor and chemist Józef Zawadzki .
Ib Rehné ( 18 January 1922 -- 7 March 2005 ) was Danish Radio 's correspondent in the Middle East for many years .

Julius Hougen ( 7 November 1906 -- 19 December 1993 ) was a Norwegian jurist and radio personality .
Sarah Stein ( July 26 , 1870 - 1953 ) was a wealthy American art collector .
Max Black ( 24 February 1909 -- 27 August 1988 ) was a British - American philosopher , who was a figure in analytic philosophy in the first half of the twentieth century .
John de Mohun , 2nd Baron Mohun , 9th feudal baron of Dunster , KG ( 1320 - -1376 ) was a founder member and the 11th Knight of the Most Noble Order of the Garter in 1348 .
William Horace de Vere Cole ( 5 May 1881 , Ballincurrig , Co. Cork , Ireland -- 25 February 1936 , Paris , France ) was an eccentric prankster and poet born in Ireland , which was then part of the United Kingdom .
John Morris Marsden ( 1857 -- 29 August 1939 ) was a British Solicitor and philatelist who was appointed to the Roll of Distinguished Philatelists in 1921 .
Wolff Jakob Lauffensteiner ( 1676 - -1754 ) was an eminent Austrian lutenist active in the Bavarian court where he spent much of his career in service to the Elector of Bavaria in Munich .
Sir William Acton , 1st Baronet ( died 22 January 1651 ) was an English merchant and Royalist .
Hadmar II of Kuenring ( c. 1140 -- 22 July 1217 ) was an Austrian ministerialis of the Kuenring family and son of Albero III of Kuenring .
John de Burnham ( died 1363 ) was an English - born judge and Crown official who spent much of his career in Ireland , holding office as Lord High Treasurer of Ireland and Chief Baron of the Irish Exchequer .
Harold Glenn Holland ( 1918 - 2002 ) was a developer from Arcadia , California who established the first franchise of amusement parks , Santa 's Village .
Johann Valentin Meder ( baptised May 3 , 1649 -- July 1719 ) was a German composer , organist , and singer .
Louis Littlepage or Lewis Littlepage ( 1762 - -1802 ) was an American diplomat , who most notably served in the royal court of the last Polish King , Stanisław August Poniatowski .
Theodore Musachi or Teodor I Muzaka was an Albanian nobleman that ruled the Lordship of Berat between 1372 and 1389 .
Valdemaras Martinkėnas ( 10 March 1965 -- 20 July 2004 ) was a Soviet and Lithuanian professional footballer and coach .
Einar Skinnarland DCM ( 27 April 1918 -- 5 December 2002 ) was a Norwegian resistance fighter during the Second World War .
János Kőrössy ( 26 December 1926 - 21 January 2013 ) was a Romanian jazz musician .
George Frederick Ives ( 17 November 1881 -- 12 April 1993 ) was a British - Canadian army veteran , who became known as the last surviving veteran of the Boer Wars .
Arnold Gerschwiler , OBE ( 28 May 1914 -- 22 August 2003 ) was a Swiss figure skating coach .
John Wrottesley , 1st Baron Wrottesley ( 4 October 1771 -- 16 March 1841 ) , known as Sir John Wrottesley , 9th Baronet , from 1787 to 1838 , was a British soldier and Member of Parliament .
Gustaf Albrecht Bror Cederström ( 21 September 1780 -- 25 December 1877 ) was a Swedish baron and lieutenant general and Minister of War .
Lorenza Ramírez de Arellano y Bartoli ( 1906 -- 1970 ) was the first wife of former Governor of Puerto Rico Luis A. Ferré and served as First Lady from 1968 until her death in 1970 .
Humphrey Forman ( 26 April 1888 -- 21 May 1923 ) played first - class cricket in two matches , one each for Cambridge University and Somerset in the 1910 cricket season .
Jan Koert ( b. 1853 , Rotterdam -- 2 February 1911 , Atlantic City ) was a Dutch - born musician , a leading solo violinist of his day in America , and concertmaster for some of the world 's greatest orchestras .

Amy Clarke , better known by her publishing name Mrs. Henry Clarke ( 17 April 1853 -- 4 March 1908 ) , was an English writer of historical fiction and children 's books .
George W. Platzman ( 1920 - 2008 ) was an American Geophysical Fluid Dynamicist .
David Morrieson Panton ( D. M. Panton ) ( April 9 , 1870 -- May 20 , 1955 ) was the pastor of Surrey Chapel , Norwich , Norfolk , UK , where he succeeded Robert Govett .
John Filson ( c. 1747 -- October 1788 ) was an American author , historian of Kentucky , pioneer , surveyor and one of the founders of Cincinnati , Ohio .
Gusu of Baekje ( died 234 , r. 214 - -234 ) was the sixth king of Baekje , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Battista Malatesta ( c. 1384 -- 1448 ) , also known as Battista di Montefeltro forename also called Baptista , was an Italian Renaissance poet .
Jane Seymour ( c. 1508 -- 24 October 1537 ) was Queen of England from 1536 to 1537 as the third wife of King Henry VIII . She succeeded Anne Boleyn as queen consort following the latter 's execution for high treason , incest , and adultery in May 1536 .
Maria Foka ( Greek : Μαρία Φωκά , d. 15 June 2001 ) was a Greek actress and participated in character roles .
Daniel Adamson ( 30 April 1820 -- 13 January 1890 ) was an English engineer who became a successful manufacturer of boilers and was the driving force behind the inception of the Manchester Ship Canal project during the 1880s .
Thomas Doolittle ( 1632?--1707 ) was an English nonconformist minister , tutor and author .
Cristoforo Mantegazza ( c. 1430 -- 1482 ) was an Italian sculptor who was active from 1464 .
Manrique Pérez de Lara ( died 1164 ) was a magnate of the Kingdom of Castile and its regent from 1158 until his death .
Oskar Adler ( 4 June 1875 -- 15 May 1955 ) was an Austrian violinist , physician and esoteric savant .
Arne Geijer ( b. 7 May 1910 , in Söderala , Söderhamn Municipality , Hälsingland , d. 27 January 1979 in Bromma , Stockholm ) was a Swedish trade union organizer .
Marquis Bảo Nghĩa Trần Bình Trọng ( Hán tự:陳平仲 ) ( 1259 - -1285 ) was a general of the Trần Dynasty well known for his heroic action in the war of Dai Viet against the second Mongol invasion .
Roger Pope ( died 1647 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1647 .
Al - Muntakhab al - Hasan ( died 936 ) was an imam of the Zaidi state in Yemen in the period 934 - 936 .
Anthony Knivet , also Anthony Knyvett or Antonie Knivet ( fl . 1591 - 1649 ) , was an English sailor who fell into Portuguese hands in Brazil , lived for a while with a native Brazilian tribe , and wrote about his adventures after his eventual return to Britain .
David Sonin ( 14 November 1935 -- 13 May 2008 ) was a music critic and arts journalist .
Salamullah Javid ( Azerbaijani : Salamulla Cavid , Persian : سلام‌الله جاوید‎ ; born 1900 in Khalkhal -- death 1986 in Tehran ) was an Iranian Azerbaijani physician and politician .
James Bowling Mozley ( 15 September 1813 -- 4 January 1878 ) was an English theologian .

Áed mac Bricc ( died 589 ) was an Irish bishop and saint .
James J. McCrea ( died 31 January 1969 ) was an Irish politician , farmer and businessman .
Jessica Harcourt ( 1906 - -1988 ) was an Australian model , author and actor , best known for playing a leading role in For the Term of His Natural Life ( 1927 ) .
Alan Clodd ( 22 May 1918 - 24 December 2002 ) was an Irish publisher , book collector , and dealer .
William Moraley ( 1698 - -1762 ) was an Englishman who emigrated to Philadelphia , Pennsylvania in 1729 as an indentured servant .
Thomas Baty ( 8 February 1869 -- 9 February 1954 ) was a British lawyer and expert on international law who spent much of his career working for the Imperial Japanese government .
Sir Maurice Charles Philip O'Connell ( also known as Maurice Charles O'Connell ) , KCH ( 1768 -- 25 May 1848 ) was a commander of forces and lieutenant - governor of colonial New South Wales .
Samuel Neilson ( 17 September 1761 -- 29 August 1803 ) was one of the founder members of the Society of United Irishmen and the founder of its newspaper the Northern Star .
Sir Harry Jephcott , 1st Baronet ( 15 January 1891 -- 29 May 1978 ) was a British pharmaceutical industrialist .
Sir William Macewen , CB , FRS , ( /məˈkjuːᵻn/ ) ( 22 June 1848 -- 22 March 1924 ) was a Scottish surgeon .
Henry Gillman ( 1833 - -1915 ) was an ethnologist , curator for the Detroit Scientific Society , a librarian at the Detroit Public Library , and later he was affiliated with Harvard University 's Peabody Museum of Archaeology and Ethnology .
Nils Uhlin Hansen ( 6 May 1919 -- 11 January 1945 ) was a Norwegian long jumper and resistance member during World War II . He had a successful athletics career before the war ; holding the Nordic record in the event .
Horace Lindrum ( born Horace Norman William Morrell , 15 January 1912 -- 20 June 1974 ) was an Australian professional snooker and billiards player .
William de Clinton , 1st Earl of Huntingdon ( c.1304 -- 31 October 1354 ) and Lord High Admiral , was the younger son of John de Clinton , 1st Baron Clinton ( d.1312/13 ) of Maxstoke Castle , Warwickshire , and Ida De Odingsells who was the granddaughter of Ida II Longespee .
The Rt . Hon . Standish O'Grady , 1st Viscount Guillamore , PC ( 1766 -- 21 April 1840 ) , from Cahir Guillamore , County Limerick , served as Lord Chief Baron of the Exchequer for Ireland for a number of years .
Keith Parris ( 31 July 1905 -- 20 August 1991 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Manno Wolf - Ferrari ( 1911 - -1994 ) was an Italian conductor , nephew of composer Ermanno Wolf - Ferrari .
John of Reading ( Latin : Johannes de Reading , Johannes Radingia , Ioannes Radingiensis ; died 1346 ) was an English Franciscan theologian and scholastic philosopher .
Elizabeth Josephine Brawley Hughes ( December 22 , 1839 -- March 1926 ) was an advocate of women 's rights in the United States West region .
Terry Scanlon ( 5 July 1913 -- 21 August 1996 ) was an Australian comedian and pantomime artist .
William Preston Phelps ( 1848 - -1917 ) , known as `` the Painter of the Monadnock '' , was an American landscape painter born on the family farm near Chesham , in what is now the Pottersville section of Dublin , New Hampshire on March 6 , 1848 to mother Mary Phelps and father Jayson Phelps .
Hubert Beckers ( 4 November 1806 -- 10 March 1889 ) was a German philosopher known chiefly as an expositor of the philosophy of Schelling .
Duane Lyman ( 1886 - 1966 ) was a Buffalo , New York - based architect considered the `` dean of Western New York Architecture . ''
Vice Admiral Sir Christopher Myngs ( 1625 - -1666 ) , English naval officer and pirate , came of a Norfolk family and was a relative of another admiral , Sir Cloudesley Shovell .
Francisca Flores ( December 1913 , San Diego California - April 1996 ) was a chicana activist and fighter against women 's oppression .
Wilfrid Thomas Reid ( 4 March 1887 - 5 April 1968 ) was an English aircraft designer and considered one of the pioneers of the Canadian aircraft industry .
Joseph Maria Pernter ( 15 March 1848 at Neumark , Tyrol -- 20 December 1908 at Arco ) was an Austrian Jesuit and scientist .
Pola Gojawiczyńska , real name Apolonia Gojawiczyńska , née Koźniewska ( 1 April 1896 -- 29 March 1963 ) was a Polish writer .
Elemér Somfay ( 28 August 1898 -- 15 May 1979 ) was a Hungarian athlete who competed mainly in the pentathlon .
Leonidas Andrianopoulos ( Greek : Λεωνίδας Ανδριανόπουλος ; 10 August 1911 -- 25 October 2011 ) was a Greek footballer who played as a striker .
Broadus Miller ( c. 1904 - -1927 ) was an African American man who in 1927 was accused of killing a young Morganton , North Carolina mill worker named Gladys Kincaid .
Yang Du ( simplified Chinese : 杨度 ; traditional Chinese : 楊度 ; pinyin : Yáng Dù ; 1875 -- 17 September 1931 ) was a Chinese politician .
Ernie Tagg ( 15 November 1917 - 29 November 2006 ) was an English professional football player and manager , particularly associated with Crewe Alexandra .
William Silver Oliver , M.D. ( 1836 , Kilfinane -- 27 April 1908 , Farnborough ) was an Irish - born Canadian military surgeon remembered for describing Oliver 's sign .
Cleve Cartmill ( 1908 - -1964 ) was an American writer of science fiction and fantasy short stories .
Thomas Macknight ( 15 February 1829 -- 19 November 1899 ) was an Anglo - Irish newspaper editor , biographer and publisher .
Miel Louw ( 26 May 1933 -- 8 December 2007 , Leuven ) was a Belgian journalist , television presenter , and writer best known on television for his documentary series Wikken en wegen between 1974 and 1991 and ABC - auto which he wrote , presented and produced for television in 1992 with Annick Van Dam .
Lajos Markos ( 1917 - -1993 ) was a Hungarian American artist trained at the Royal Academy of Budapest .
Charles Frederick Williams ( 4 May 1838 -- 9 February 1904 ) , was a Scottish - Irish writer , journalist , and war correspondent .
William Lodge ( July 4 , 1649 -- 1689 ) was an English engraver and printmaker of the Baroque period .
Angélique Arvanitaki ( 11 July 1901 -- 6 October 1983 ) was a French neurophysiologist who did research on the electrical activity of neurons using the large nerve fibres of several different molluscs .
Henry Dwight Barrows ( 1825 - -1914 ) was an American teacher , businessman , farmer , goldminer , reporter , United States Marshal , Los Angeles County School Superintendent , manufacturer , writer , and a founder and president of the Historical Society of Southern California .
Robert Whymant ( 29 November 1944 -- 26 December 2004 ) was a British writer and reporter .
V. K. Madhavan Kutty ( Malayalam : വീ കെ മാധവന്‍കുട്ടി ; 1934 - -2005 ) was an eminent journalist from the state of Kerala , India .
Trevor Clay , CBE , FRCN ( 10 May 1936 in Nuneaton , Warwickshire , England -- 23 April 1994 in Harefield , Middlesex , England ) was a British nurse and former General Secretary of the Royal College of Nursing .
Robert Plot ( 13 December 1640 -- 30 April 1696 ) was an English naturalist , first Professor of Chemistry at the University of Oxford , and the first keeper of the Ashmolean Museum .
Louise Emerson Ronnebeck ( 25 August 1901 -- 17 February 1980 ) was an American painter best known for her murals executed for the Works Progress Administration ( WPA ) .
Sir Clement Edmondes ( c. 1568 - -1622 ) was an English government official and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1609 and 1622 .
William Isaac Last AMICE ( 1857 -- 7 August 1911 ) was a British mechanical engineer who became a museum curator and the second Director of the Science Museum in London .
Annette Rogers Kelly ( 22 October 1913 -- 8 November 2006 ) was an American sprinter who competed mainly in the 100 metres .
Adam Falckenhagen ( 26 April 1697 -- 6 October 1754 ) was a German lutenist and composer of the Baroque period .
Lauro Amadò ( 3 March 1912 -- 6 June 1971 ) , aka Lajo , was a Swiss football player .
Sun Du ( traditional Chinese : 孫渡 ; simplified Chinese : 孙渡 ; pinyin : Sūn Dù ; 1898 - -1967 ) was a Kuomintang general from Yunnan .
Don Rubbo ( December 5 , 1926 -- January 1979 ) was a mentor and guide of Peter Max and an affiliate of Andy Warhol in the mid-1960s .
Samuel Morison Brown ( February 1817 - 20 September 1856 ) , Scottish chemist , poet and essayist .
Ernald ( or Ærnald ) ( † 1163 ) was the second Abbot of Kelso before becoming Bishop of Cell Rígmonaid ( St Andrews ) , the highest ranking Scottish see in the period .
Topal Osman Pasha ( 1663 - -1733 ) was an Ottoman military officer and administrator .
Judd Marmor ( 2 May 1910 -- 16 December 2003 ) was an American psychiatrist known for his role in removing homosexuality from the American Psychiatric Association Diagnostic and Statistical Manual of Mental Disorders .
Jeni Bojilova - Pateva ( bulg . Жени Божилова-Патева ; December 1878 - 17 June 1955 ) is a Bulgarian human rights activists .
Sir William Meredith , 3rd Baronet ( c.1725 -- 2 January 1790 ) was a British politician of the late 18th Century , one of the Rockingham Whigs .
Guang Qin ( 廣欽 , 1892 - -1986 ) was a renowned Buddhist monk , teacher and cultivator .
Gugsa Araya Selassie ( 1885 -- 28 April 1932 ) was an army commander and a member of the royal family of the Ethiopian Empire .
Gregorios Xenopoulos (; December 9 , 1867 -- 14 January 1951 ) was a novelist , journalist and writer of plays from Zakynthos .
John Beirne , Jnr ( died 23 October 1967 ) was an Irish Clann na Talmhan politician .
Frederick Octavius Pickard - Cambridge ( 3 November 1860 -- 9 February 1905 ) was an English arachnologist .
Henry James , 1st Baron James of Hereford GCVO PC QC ( 30 October 1828 -- 18 August 1911 ) , known as Sir Henry James between 1873 and 1895 , was an Anglo - Welsh lawyer and statesman .
Novica Čanović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Новица Чановић ; 29 November 1961 -- 3 July 1993 ) was a Serb high jumper .
Wilbur Marshall Urban ( 1873 - -1952 ) was an American philosopher of language , influenced by Ernst Cassirer .
Ali Jawad Al Taher ( 1911?/1922 ? -- 10 October 1996 ) was an Iraqi critic and literary scholar .
Dan Apostol ( 12 July 1957 Bucharest -- 4 March 2013 Bucharest ) was a Romanian writer and researcher , specialized in several border domains of aviation , history , archeology , ancient civilisations , art , biology , anthropology , palaeontology and cryptozoology .
Thomas Tropenell , sometimes Tropenelle and Tropnell ( c. 1405 -- 1488 ) , was an English lawyer and landowner in Wiltshire in the west of England .
Moses A. McLaughlin ( 1834 - 1899 ) Irish born , California Militia officer , Union Army officer , farmer , later a doctor .
Marie - Jean - Augustin Vestris , known as Auguste Vestris ( 27 March 1760 - 5 December 1842 ) , was a French dancer .
Frank Durkan ( 1930 -- 2006 ) was an Irish - American attorney best known for having represented numerous members of the Provisional Irish Republican Army ( IRA ) , including avowed gun - runner and pivotal North American member of the IRA George Harrison , who stood trial , and was acquitted , in 1982 .
Pedro Sánchez de Castro , ( fl . 1454 - 1484 ) was a Spanish Gothic painter .
Cornelius Loos ( 1546 -- February 3 , 1595 ) , also known as Cornelius Losaeus Callidius , was a Roman Catholic priest , theologian , and professor of theology , and was the first Catholic official to write publicly against the witch trials then raging throughout Europe .
Delphin Strungk ( or Strunck ) ( 1600 or 1601 -- 12 October 1694 ) was a German composer and organist associated with the North German school .
Ideal Petrov died in his home city of Varna on 20 September 1983 .
Huguet de Mataplana ( after 1173 -- 28 November 1213 ) was a Catalan nobleman and poet .
Izet Dibra ( 1878 - 1964 ) born Izet Shatku was an Albanian politician and mayor of Tirana from 1927 to 1928 .
Robert Dibble ( 15 November 1882 - 1963 ) was an English rugby union international who represented England from 1906 to 1912 .
Charles James Roberts C.M.G. , ( 29 March 1846 -- 14 August 1925 ) was a publican and politician in colonial New South Wales and Postmaster - General of New South Wales .
Reverend John Warneford MA , BD ( 1720 -- 20 November 1773 ) was an English clergyman and scholar .
Michael Garber ( 1892 - 1977 ) was a Montreal based lawyer and a Canadian Jewish community activist .
Urani Rumbo ( 1895 - 1936 ) was an Albanian feminist , teacher and playwright .
Emanuel Wirth ( 18 October 1842 -- 5 January 1923 ) was a German violinist and violist .
Boris Stavrev ( Bulgarian : Борис Ставрев , 7 March 1935 -- 16 May 2003 ) was a Bulgarian fencer .
Walter Sherard Vines ( 1890 -- 1974 ) was an English writer and academic who wrote poetry , novels , and criticism .
Ambassador Mohammed Lawal Rafindadi ( 1934 - 2007 ) was a Nigerian diplomat and security chief from Katsina state .
Ulysses Grant Dailey ( 1885 - -1961 ) was an American surgeon , writer , and teacher .
Henri de Bailly ( died October 1637 ) was a French composer .
Big Bill Neidjie ( c. 1920 -- 23 May 2002 ) was the last surviving speaker of the Gaagudju language , an indigenous language from northern Kakadu after which the World Heritage - listed Kakadu National Park is named .
Giovanni Pettenella ( 28 March 1943 -- 19 February 2010 ) was an Italian track cyclist .
Charlie Lees ( 1887 - 1976 ) was a pioneer rugby league player in the Australian competition - the NSWRFL .
Yiannis Vasiliadis ( Greek : Γιάννης Βασιλειάδης ; 1924 -- 30 March 2012 ) was a Greek politician and former naval admiral who served as a Member of Parliament from 1985 to 1993 .
James Brown Lord ( 26 April 1859 -- 1 June 1902 ) was an American architect , working in a Beaux - Arts idiom , with a practice in New York City .
André Eugène Marcel Pourchier ( 1 June 1897 -- 1 September 1944 ) was a French military officer whose last rank was Lieutenant - Colonel .
Major General Robert Sedgwick ( c. 1611 -- 1656 ) was an English colonist , born 1611 in Woburn , Bedfordshire , England , and baptised on 6 May 1613 .
Ron Baggott ( 16 January 1917 - -28 April 2013 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Iqbal Masih ( Punjabi , Urdu : اقبال مسیح ; born : 1983 , died : 16 April 1995 ) was a Pakistani child who became a symbol of abusive child labor in the developing world .
Count János Forgách de Ghymes et Gács ( German : Johann Graf Forgách von Ghymes und Gács ) ( 24 October 1870 -- 25 September 1935 ) , was an Austro - Hungarian diplomat of Hungarian origin who played a prominent role during World War I and in particular the July Crisis .
Iosef Mikhailovich Oranski ( 24 April 1923 - 16 May 1977 ) , sometimes spelled Iosef Mikhailovich Oranskii , was a prominent Soviet linguist affiliated with the Leningrad Institute of Oriental Studies .
Sir John Rankine Goody , FBA ( /ˈɡʊdi/ ; 27 July 1919 -- 16 July 2015 ) , known as Jack Goody , was a British social anthropologist .
Edmund Henry Gilpin ( 1876 -- 24 July 1950 ) , known as Harry Gilpin , was a British politician and company director .
Aubrey Darmody ( 17 May 1921 -- 9 February 2006 ) was a Welsh footballer who played in the Football League as a full - back for Norwich City .
Maxim Mazumdar ( 1952 -- 28 April 1988 ) was an Indo - Canadian playwright and director .
George of Antioch ( died 1151 or 1152 ) was the first true ammiratus ammiratorum , successor of the great Christodulus .
Matti Merivirta ( 21 October 1866 , Pori - 7 September 1944 ; born Mathias Sjöström ) was a Finnish Lutheran clergyman and politician .
Nora Thompson Dean ( 1907 - -1984 ) , also known as Weenjipahkihelexkwe , which translates as `` Touching Leaves Woman '' in Unami , was a member of the Delaware Tribe of Indians .
William H. Illingworth ( 1844 - -1893 ) was an English photographer who accompanied both Captain James L. Fisk 's 1866 expedition to the Montana Territory and Lt . Colonel George Custer 's 1874 U.S. military expedition into the Black Hills of the Dakota Territory ( now western South Dakota ) .
Gustav Nezval ( 18 November 1907 -- 17 September 1998 ) by civil name Augustin Nezval , was a Czech stage and film actor .
Warren Tartaglia ( aka Walid al - Taha ) ( March 13 , 1944 - November 1965 ) was a jazz musician , poet and one of the six founders of the Moorish Orthodox Church of America .
Bernard G. Amend ( 1 January 1821 -- 6 April 1911 ) was a German - born pharmacist .
Richard Christopher Carrington ( 26 May 1826 -- 27 November 1875 ) was an English amateur astronomer whose 1859 astronomical observations demonstrated the existence of solar flares as well as suggesting their electrical influence upon the Earth and its aurorae ; and whose 1863 records of sunspot observations revealed the differential rotation of the Sun .
Hans Vollenweider ( 11 February 1908 - 18 October 1940 ) was a Swiss criminal .
Maria Ivanovna Khlopova ( died 1633 ) , was a Russian noble , the fiancee of Tsar Michael I of Russia .
Casimiro Castro ( 24 April 1826 Tepetlaoxtoc - 8 January 1889 Mexico City ) , was a Mexican painter and lithographer , and is regarded as having been a leading graphic and landscape artist in nineteenth century Mexico .
Felix Ehrlich ( born 1 June 1877 in Harriehausen ( today incorporated in Bad Gandersheim ) , died in 1942 in Obernigk near Breslau ) was a German chemist and biochemist .
Henry Condell ( baptised 5 September 1576-died December 1627 ) was an actor in the King 's Men , the playing company for which William Shakespeare wrote .
Bonifacio del Carril ( 14 April 1911 -- 23 December 1994 ) was an Argentine writer , lawyer , diplomat , and historian .
Henrietta Maria Rice , Emma Fitch Rice , Mary Wood Rice , James Stephen Rice , and Harvey Rice , Jr. Harvey Rice died on 7 November 1891 in Cleveland and was buried at Cleveland 's Lake View Cemetery .
Isaac Kimber ( 1692 - -1755 ) was an English General Baptist minister , biographer , and journalist .
Joseph Tomlinson ( 11 November 1823 London -- 22 April 1894 ) was a British railroad engineer , and executive .
Artaldus who live the remainder of his days at Arvières , living until the age of 105 , he died in 1206 .
Bernard Peyrilhe ( 1737 - -1804 ) was a French surgeon known as one of the founders of experimental cancer research .

Hedayatollah Hatami ( c. 1914 - September 1988 ) was an Iranian man who was allegedly hanged during the 1988 executions of Iranian political prisoners .
William FitzAlan , 18th Earl of Arundel , 8th Baron Maltravers KG ( 1476 -- 23 January 1544 ) was an English peer , styled as Lord Maltravers from 1487 to 1524 .
Brewster Hughes ( 12 December 1912 -- 30 September 1986 ) , born Ignatius Abiodun Oke and who later used the name Ernest Henley Oke Hughes , was a Nigerian guitarist , bandleader and community leader who was active in Britain as a highlife performer and recording artist after the Second World War .
Sayyid Mohammad Kazem Shariatmadari ( Azerbaijani : Məhəmməd Kazım Şəriətmədari , Persian : محمد کاظم شریعتمداری‎‎ ) , also spelled Shariat - Madari ( 1905 -- 3 April 1986 ) , was an Iranian Grand Ayatollah .
Robin Bryans ( 24 April 1928 -- 11 June 2005 ) , born Robert Harbinson Bryans , was a prolific author of popular travel and autobiographical works under the pen names Robin Bryans , Robert Harbinson , and Donald Cameron .
William Brunsdon Yapp ( 1909 -- 1990 ) was a zoologist and author .
Robert Woodcock ( bap . 9 October 1690 -- died 10 April 1728 ) was an English marine painter , musician , and composer who lived during the Baroque period .
Frank Hardcastle ( 12 May 1844 - 6 November 1908 ) was a bleacher and businessman and Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1885 to 1892 .
Heather Thatcher ( 3 September 1896 -- 15 February 1987 ) was an English actress in theatre and films .
Ray Jessel ( born Raymond Jessel , 16 October 1929 -- 17 July 2015 ) was a Welsh songwriter , orchestrator , and musical theatre composer .
Ignác Šechtl ( 26 May 1840 -- 6 July 1911 ) , also known as Ignace Schächtl or Hynek Šechtl , was a pioneer of Czech photography ( especially photojournalism ) and cinematography .
Esther Howard ( 4 April 1892 -- 8 March 1965 ) was a stage and film character actress who played a wide range of supporting roles , from man - hungry spinsters to amoral criminals , appearing in 108 films in her 23-year career .
Jane Heap ( 1883 -- 1964 ) was an American publisher and a significant figure in the development and promotion of literary modernism .
Albert Elias ( 16 May 1971 in Dallas - 18 December 2012 ) was an American NFL agent and chairman of the Elias Sports Management .
P. Patrick McKernan ( April 19 , 1941 - July 10 , 2001 ) was one of the pioneers of minor league baseball .
Nemacolin died on the island in 1767 , and European settlers soon laid claim to that land .
Michael Laurence ( 1935 - 23 March 2015 ) was an Australian actor , producer writer best known for creating Return to Eden .
Christian Thomasius ( 1 January 1655 -- 23 September 1728 ) was a German jurist and philosopher .
Capt . Edward Levett Darwin ( 12 April 1821 -- 23 April 1901 ) was the author under the pen - name High Elms of Gameskeeper 's Manual , a guide for gamekeepers on large estates which shows keen observation of the habits of various animals .
Emanuel Witz ( 27 June 1717 -- 11 December 1797 ) was a Swiss painter , born in Biel .
Edward Wetenhall ( 1636 - -1713 ) was an English bishop of the Church of Ireland .
Erwin Axer ( 1 January 1917 -- 5 August 2012 ) was a Polish theatre director , writer and university professor .
Heathoberht ( Heathubeorht or Hathoberht ; died 801 ) was a medieval Bishop of London .
Saihei Hirose ( June 16 , 1828 -- 1914 ) was a Japanese mining businessman and former head of the board of directors of Sumitomo Zaibatsu from 1877 to 1894 .
Mary Hemings , also known as Mary Hemings Bell ( 1753-after 1834 ) , was born into slavery , most likely in Charles City County , Virginia , as the oldest child of Elizabeth Hemings , a mixed - race slave held by John Wayles .
Horrie Clover ( 20 March 1895 -- 1 January 1984 ) was a leading Australian rules footballer in the ( then ) Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Hana Meisel ( Hebrew : חנה מייזל‎ , born 25 December 1883 , died 1972 ) was a Jewish agronomist , feminist and Zionist .
John Wallop , Viscount Lymington ( 3 August 1718 -- 19 November 1749 ) was a British politician , styled Hon . John Wallop from 1720 to 1743 .
Philip of Spanheim ( also : Philip of Sponheim ; † 22 . July 1279 ) was elected Archbishop of Salzburg ( 1247 - -1257 ) and Patriarch of Aquileia ( 1269 - -1271 ) .
Mary Harper Sowell ( 1924 - 2005 ) , was an Arkansas poet who deeply loved the Ozark Mountains and the people who lived there .

Rewani , ( c.1475 - 1524 ) , Ilyas Shudja Celebi , was an Ottoman poet .

Alexei Kondratiev ( 1949 - -2010 ) was an American author , linguist , and teacher of Celtic languages , folklore and culture .
Robert Amadas ( before 1490 -- 7 April 1532 ) was a London Goldsmith whose clients included King Henry VIII and his courtiers .
Jacopino della Scala ( died 1215 ) , an Italian merchant and politician , was a member of the Scaliger family of future lords of Verona .
Robert Stamm ( 16 July 1900 -- 4 November 1937 ) was a German politician , a Communist ( KPD ) member of the Reichstag from Bremen , and a victim of the Nazi régime .
Charles Spencer Denman , 5th Baron Denman , 2nd Baronet CBE MC TD ( 7 July 1916 -- 21 November 2012 ) was a British businessman .

Jay Kirby ( January 28 , 1920 -- July 30 , 1964 ) was an American actor in films and television .
Juan López de Palacios Rubios ( 1450 - -1524 ) was a Spanish jurist whose real name is Juan Lopez de Vivero .
Bessica Faith Raiche née Medlar , known as Bessie Raiche , ( April 1875 -- 11 April 1932 ) was a dentist , businesswoman , and physician , who was the first woman in the United States accredited with flying solo in an airplane .
Henry Prentiss ( 1801 - -1859 ) manufactured musical instruments , umbrellas and sheet music , which he sold from his shop on Court Street in Boston , Massachusetts in the 19th - century .

Cú Ceanain Ó Con Ceanainn,(died 1224 ) was King of Uí Díarmata , Ireland .

Katherine Austen ( 1629 -- ca . 1683 ) was a British diarist and poet best known for Book M , her manuscript collection of meditations , journal entries , and verse .
Walter Rice Howell Powell ( 1819 - 26 June 1889 ) was a Welsh landowner and Liberal politician .
Alfred Pontifex ( 17 March 1842 -- 25 August 1930 ) was an English first - class cricketer who made a single appearance for Gloucestershire County Cricket Club in 1871 .
Colm Ó Lochlainn ( 1892 - 26 June 1972 ) was a printer , typographer , collector of Irish ballads and traditional Irish Uilleann piper .
Wallace Mercer ( 4 June 1946 -- 17 January 2006 ) was chairman of the Scottish football club Heart of Midlothian from 1981 to 1994 .
James Dennis , 1st Baron Tracton PC ( 1721 - -15 June 1782 ) was an Irish politician and judge .

Doris Hanson ( October 24 , 1925 - -November 8 , 2006 ) was a Wisconsin politician and real estate broker .

Paddy Mullins ( 1919 -- 28 October 2010 ) was an Irish racehorse trainer in a career which spanned fifty two years .
Farinelli ( Italian pronunciation : ( fariˈnɛlːi ) ) ( 24 January 1705 -- 16 September 1782 ) , was the stage name of Carlo Maria Michelangelo Nicola Broschi ( pronounced ( ˈkarlo ˈbrɔski ) ) , celebrated Italian castrato singer of the 18th century and one of the greatest singers in the history of opera .
Alasdair Crotach MacLeod ( Scottish Gaelic : Alasdair Crotach MacLeòid ) ( 1450 -- 1547 ) is considered to be the eighth chief of Scottish Clan MacLeod .

Claude Grahame - White ( 21 August 1879 -- 19 August 1959 ) was an English pioneer of aviation , and the first to make a night flight , during the Daily Mail sponsored 1910 London to Manchester air race .

Jacopo Coppi called `` ' Jacopo del Meglio ' '' ( `` the Best '' ) ( Peretola , 1523 - 1591 ) was an Italian painter , mainly active in Florence in a Mannerist style .
Roger Vandercruse Lacroix ( 1728 - -1799 ) , often known as Roger Vandercruse , was a Parisian ébéniste whose highly refined furniture spans the rococo and the early neoclassical styles .
Vafa Guluzade ( surname also spelled as Gulizade(h ) , Goulizade(h ) , Kulizade(h ) , Quluzade(h ) ) ( Azerbaijani : Vəfa Mirzağa oğlu Quluzadə ) ( 21 December 1940 -- 1 May 2015 ) was an Azerbaijani diplomat , political scientist and specialist in conflict resolution .

Salvarino Aliprandi ( died 1344 ) was an Italian Legal Counsel of the 14th century .
Andrew Allam ( 1655 -- 17 June 1685 ) was an English academic and miscellaneous writer .
George Mackenzie , 3rd Earl of Cromartie ( c. 1703 - -28 September 1766 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Arthur Montford ( 25 May 1929 -- 26 November 2014 ) was a Scottish Television sports journalist , best known for his 32-year tenure as the presenter of Scottish Television 's Scotsport .
William Coward ( 1657?--1725 ) was an English physician , controversial writer , and poet .
Constance of Greater Poland ( also known as of Poznań ) ( Polish : Konstancja wielkopolska ( poznańska ) ) ( 1245/46 -- 8 October 1281 ) was a princess of Greater Poland , a member of the House of Piast , and by marriage a Margravine of Brandenburg - Stendal .
Paul Ragueneau ( 18 March 1608 -- 3 September 1680 ) is known most notable as a Catholic Jesuit missionary .
Robert Scott Burn ( 14 February 1825 -- 31 January 1901 ) was a Scottish engineer and author , known as prolific writer between 1850 and 1860 on a wide range of subjects ranging from agriculture , building construction and mechanical engineering to architectural and technical drawing .
Dirck Storm ( 1630 - -1716 ) was an early colonial American famous for composing the history of the Dutch community at Sleepy Hollow and beginning the community 's records .
Harry Scott Bennett ( 1 June 1877 -- 24 May 1959 ) , originally Henry Gilbert Scott Bennett , was an Australian socialist speaker and organiser .
John Keble ( 25 April 1792 -- 29 March 1866 ) was an English churchman and poet , one of the leaders of the Oxford Movement .
Alexander Lawton Mackall ( Chestnut Hill , Philadelphia , Pennsylvania , May 23 , 1888 -- West New Brighton , Staten Island , New York , 1968 ) was an author , journalist and gastronomy expert and critic .
Fu Youde ( Chinese : 傅友德 ; Wade -- Giles : Fu Yu - te ) ( d. 20 December 1394 ) was a Chinese general and a highly competent commander in the Ming navy .
